dicated to the overthrow of the State. The Brotherhood, its\"}]","[{\"text\":\"also whispered stories of a terrible\"},{\"text\":\"book, a compendium of all the heresies, of which Goldstein was the author\"},{\"text\":\"and which circulated clandestinely here and there. It was a book without a\"},{\"text\":\"title. People referred to it, if at all, simply as THE BOOK. But one knew\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of such things only through vague rumours. Neither the Brotherhood nor\"},{\"text\":\"THE BOOK was a subject that any ordinary Party member would mention if\"},{\"text\":\"there was a way of avoiding it.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"were leaping up and\"},{\"text\":\"down in their places and shouting at the tops of their voices in an effort\"},{\"text\":\"to drown the maddening bleating voice that came from the screen. The little\"},{\"text\":\"sandy-haired woman had turned bright pink, and her mouth was opening and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"shutting like that of a landed fish. Even O'Brien's heavy face was flushed.\"},{\"text\":\"He was sitting very straight in his chair, his powerful chest swelling and\"},{\"text\":\"quivering as though he were standing up to the assault of a wave. The\"}]","[{\"text\":\"begun crying out 'Swine! Swine! Swine!'\"},{\"text\":\"and suddenly she picked up a heavy Newspeak dictionary and flung it at the\"},{\"text\":\"screen. It struck Goldstein's nose and bounced off; the voice continued\"}]","[{\"text\":\"shouting with the\"},{\"text\":\"others and kicking his heel violently against the rung of his chair. The\"},{\"text\":\"horrible thing about the Two Minutes Hate was not that one was obliged to\"},{\"text\":\"act a part, but, on the contrary, that it was impossible to avoid joining\"}]","[{\"text\":\"seconds any pretence was always unnecessary. A hideous\"},{\"text\":\"ecstasy of fear and vindictiveness, a desire to kill, to torture, to smash\"},{\"text\":\"faces in with a sledge-hammer, seemed to flow through the whole group of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"against one's will into\"},{\"text\":\"a grimacing, screaming lunatic. And yet the rage that one felt was an\"},{\"text\":\"abstract, undirected emotion which could be switched from one object to\"},{\"text\":\"another like the flame of a blowlamp. Thus, at one moment Winston's hatred\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was not turned against Goldstein at all, but, on the contrary, against\"},{\"text\":\"Big Brother, the Party, and the Thought Police; and at such moments his\"},{\"text\":\"heart went out to the lonely, derided heretic on the screen, sole guardian\"}]","[{\"text\":\"lies. And yet the very next instant he\"},{\"text\":\"was at one with the people about him, and all that was said of Goldstein\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to him to be true. At those moments his secret loathing of Big\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to tower up, an\"},{\"text\":\"invincible, fearless protector, standing like a rock against the hordes\"},{\"text\":\"of Asia, and Goldstein, in spite of his isolation, his helplessness, and\"},{\"text\":\"the doubt that hung about his very existence, seemed like some sinister\"}]","[{\"text\":\"by the mere power of his voice of wrecking the structure\"},{\"text\":\"of civilization.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"It was even possible, at moments, to switch one's hatred this way or that\"},{\"text\":\"by a voluntary act. Suddenly, by the sort of violent effort with which one\"}]","[{\"text\":\"head away from the pillow in a nightmare, Winston succeeded\"},{\"text\":\"in transferring his hatred from the face on the screen to the dark-haired\"},{\"text\":\"girl behind him. Vivid, beautiful hallucinations flashed through his mind.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"rubber truncheon. He would tie her naked\"},{\"text\":\"to a stake and shoot her full of arrows like Saint Sebastian. He would\"},{\"text\":\"ravish her and cut her throat at the moment of climax. Better than before,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hated her because\"},{\"text\":\"she was young and pretty and sexless, because he wanted to go to bed with\"},{\"text\":\"her and would never do so, because round her sweet supple waist, which\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to ask you to encircle it with your arm, there was only the odious\"}]","[{\"text\":\"aggressive symbol of chastity.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The Hate rose to its climax. The voice of Goldstein had become an actual\"},{\"text\":\"sheep's bleat, and for an instant the face changed into that of a sheep.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"soldier who seemed\"},{\"text\":\"to be advancing, huge and terrible, his sub-machine gun roaring, and\"},{\"text\":\"seeming to spring out of the surface of the screen, so that some of the\"},{\"text\":\"people in the front row actually flinched backwards in their seats. But\"}]","[{\"text\":\"moment, drawing a deep sigh of relief from everybody, the\"},{\"text\":\"hostile figure melted into the face of Big Brother, black-haired,\"},{\"text\":\"black-moustachio'd, full of power and mysterious calm, and so vast that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Nobody heard what Big Brother was saying.\"},{\"text\":\"It was merely a few words of encouragement, the sort of words that are\"},{\"text\":\"uttered in the din of battle, not distinguishable individually but\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the face of Big\"},{\"text\":\"Brother faded away again, and instead the three slogans of the Party stood\"},{\"text\":\"out in bold capitals:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"WAR IS PEACE\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"FREEDOM IS SLAVERY\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"GNORANCE IS STRENGTH\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"But the face of Big Brother seemed to persist for several seconds on the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"had made on everyone's eyeballs was\"},{\"text\":\"too vivid to wear off immediately. The little sandy-haired woman had flung\"},{\"text\":\"herself forward over the back of the chair in front of her. With a\"},{\"text\":\"tremulous murmur that sounded like 'My Saviour!' she extended her arms\"}]","[{\"text\":\"towards the screen. Then she buried her face in her hands. It was apparent\"},{\"text\":\"that she was uttering a prayer.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"At this moment the entire group of people broke into a deep, slow,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"very slowly, with a\"},{\"text\":\"long pause between the first 'B' and the second--a heavy, murmurous sound,\"},{\"text\":\"somehow curiously savage, in the background of which one seemed to hear the\"},{\"text\":\"stamp of naked feet and the throbbing of tom-toms. For perhaps as much as\"}]","[{\"text\":\"thirty seconds they kept it up. It was a refrain that was often heard in\"},{\"text\":\"moments of overwhelming emotion. Partly it was a sort of hymn to the wisdom\"},{\"text\":\"and majesty of Big Brother, but still more it was an act of self-hypnosis,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"consciousness by means of rhythmic noise.\"},{\"text\":\"Winston's entrails seemed to grow cold. In the Two Minutes Hate he could\"},{\"text\":\"not help sharing in the general delirium, but this sub-human chanting of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"he chanted with the\"},{\"text\":\"rest: it was impossible to do otherwise. To dissemble your feelings, to\"},{\"text\":\"control your face, to do what everyone else was doing, was an instinctive\"},{\"text\":\"reaction. But there was a space of a couple of seconds during which the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"expression of his eyes might conceivably have betrayed him. And it was\"},{\"text\":\"exactly at this moment that the significant thing happened--if, indeed,\"},{\"text\":\"it did happen.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Momentarily he caught O'Brien's eye. O'Brien had stood up. He had taken\"}]","[{\"text\":\"off his spectacles and was in the act of resettling them on his nose with\"},{\"text\":\"his characteristic gesture. But there was a fraction of a second when\"},{\"text\":\"their eyes met, and for as long as it took to happen Winston knew--yes, he\"}]","[{\"text\":\"same thing as himself. An unmistakable\"},{\"text\":\"message had passed. It was as though their two minds had opened and the\"},{\"text\":\"thoughts were flowing from one into the other through their eyes. 'I am\"}]","[{\"text\":\"precisely what you\"},{\"text\":\"are feeling. I know all about your contempt, your hatred, your disgust.\"},{\"text\":\"But don't worry, I am on your side!' And then the flash of intelligence\"},{\"text\":\"was gone, and O'Brien's face was as inscrutable as everybody else's.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"That was all, and he was already uncertain whether it had happened. Such\"},{\"text\":\"incidents never had any sequel. All that they did was to keep alive in him\"},{\"text\":\"the belief, or hope, that others besides himself were the enemies of the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"underground conspiracies were true after\"},{\"text\":\"all--perhaps the Brotherhood really existed! It was impossible, in spite\"},{\"text\":\"of the endless arrests and confessions and executions, to be sure that the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in it, some days\"},{\"text\":\"not. There was no evidence, only fleeting glimpses that might mean anything\"},{\"text\":\"or nothing: snatches of overheard conversation, faint scribbles on lavatory\"},{\"text\":\"walls--once, even, when two strangers met, a small movement of the hand\"}]","[{\"text\":\"as though it might be a signal of recognition. It was all\"},{\"text\":\"guesswork: very likely he had imagined everything. He had gone back to his\"},{\"text\":\"cubicle without looking at O'Brien again. The idea of following up their\"}]","[{\"text\":\"mind. It would have been inconceivably\"},{\"text\":\"dangerous even if he had known how to set about doing it. For a second, two\"},{\"text\":\"seconds, they had exchanged an equivocal glance, and that was the end of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"locked loneliness in\"},{\"text\":\"which one had to live.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston roused himself and sat up straighter. He let out a belch. The gin\"},{\"text\":\"was rising from his stomach.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"discovered that while he sat helplessly\"},{\"text\":\"musing he had also been writing, as though by automatic action. And it was\"},{\"text\":\"no longer the same cramped, awkward handwriting as before. His pen had slid\"}]","[{\"text\":\"neat capitals--\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"DOWN WITH BIG BROTHER\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"DOWN WITH BIG BROTHER\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"BROTHER\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"DOWN WITH BIG BROTHER\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"OWN WITH BIG BROTHER\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"page.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He could not help feeling a twinge of panic. It was absurd, since the\"},{\"text\":\"writing of those particular words was not more dangerous than the initial\"},{\"text\":\"act of opening the diary, but for a moment he was tempted to tear out the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"spoiled pages and abandon the enterprise altogether.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He did not do so, however, because he knew that it was useless. Whether he\"},{\"text\":\"wrote DOWN WITH BIG BROTHER, or whether he refrained from writing it, made\"}]","[{\"text\":\"with the diary, or whether he did not go\"},{\"text\":\"on with it, made no difference. The Thought Police would get him just the\"},{\"text\":\"same. He had committed--would still have committed, even if he had never\"}]","[{\"text\":\"others in itself.\"},{\"text\":\"Thoughtcrime, they called it. Thoughtcrime was not a thing that could be\"},{\"text\":\"concealed for ever. You might dodge successfully for a while, even for\"},{\"text\":\"years, but sooner or later they were bound to get you.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"night--the arrests invariably happened at night. The\"},{\"text\":\"sudden jerk out of sleep, the rough hand shaking your shoulder, the lights\"},{\"text\":\"glaring in your eyes, the ring of hard faces round the bed. In the vast\"}]","[{\"text\":\"arrest. People\"},{\"text\":\"simply disappeared, always during the night. Your name was removed from the\"},{\"text\":\"registers, every record of everything you had ever done was wiped out, your\"},{\"text\":\"one-time existence was denied and then forgotten. You were abolished,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"VAPORIZED was the usual word.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"For a moment he was seized by a kind of hysteria. He began writing in a\"},{\"text\":\"hurried untidy scrawl:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"theyll shoot me i don't care theyll shoot me in the back of the neck i\"},{\"text\":\"dont care down with big brother they always shoot you in the back of the\"},{\"text\":\"neck i dont care down with big brother----\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"chair, slightly ashamed of himself, and laid down\"},{\"text\":\"the pen. The next moment he started violently. There was a knocking at\"},{\"text\":\"the door.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Already! He sat as still as a mouse, in the futile hope that whoever it was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"after a single attempt. But no, the knocking was repeated.\"},{\"text\":\"The worst thing of all would be to delay. His heart was thumping like a\"},{\"text\":\"drum, but his face, from long habit, was probably expressionless. He got\"},{\"text\":\"up and moved heavily towards the door.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Chapter 2\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"As he put his hand to the door-knob Winston saw that he had left the\"},{\"text\":\"diary open on the table. DOWN WITH BIG BROTHER was written all over it,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"legible across the room. It was an\"},{\"text\":\"inconceivably stupid thing to have done. But, he realized, even in his\"},{\"text\":\"panic he had not wanted to smudge the creamy paper by shutting the book\"},{\"text\":\"while the ink was wet.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"breath and opened the door. Instantly a warm wave of relief\"},{\"text\":\"flowed through him. A colourless, crushed-looking woman, with wispy hair\"},{\"text\":\"and a lined face, was standing outside.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"whining sort of voice, 'I thought I\"},{\"text\":\"heard you come in. Do you think you could come across and have a look at\"},{\"text\":\"our kitchen sink? It's got blocked up and----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"It was Mrs Parsons, the wife of a neighbour on the same floor. ('Mrs' was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a word somewhat discountenanced by the Party--you were supposed to call\"},{\"text\":\"everyone 'comrade'--but with some women one used it instinctively.) She was\"},{\"text\":\"a woman of about thirty, but looking much older. One had the impression\"}]","[{\"text\":\"her face. Winston followed her down\"},{\"text\":\"the passage. These amateur repair jobs were an almost daily irritation.\"},{\"text\":\"Victory Mansions were old flats, built in 1930 or thereabouts, and were\"},{\"text\":\"falling to pieces. The plaster flaked constantly from ceilings and walls,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the pipes burst in every hard frost, the roof leaked whenever there was\"},{\"text\":\"snow, the heating system was usually running at half steam when it was not\"},{\"text\":\"closed down altogether from motives of economy. Repairs, except what you\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sanctioned by remote committees which\"},{\"text\":\"were liable to hold up even the mending of a window-pane for two years.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Of course it's only because Tom isn't home,' said Mrs Parsons vaguely.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston's, and dingy in a different\"},{\"text\":\"way. Everything had a battered, trampled-on look, as though the\"},{\"text\":\"place had just been visited by some large violent animal. Games\"},{\"text\":\"impedimenta--hockey-sticks, boxing-gloves, a burst football, a pair of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sweaty shorts turned inside out--lay all over the floor, and on the\"},{\"text\":\"table there was a litter of dirty dishes and dog-eared exercise-books.\"},{\"text\":\"On the walls were scarlet banners of the Youth League and the Spies, and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"There was the usual boiled-cabbage\"},{\"text\":\"smell, common to the whole building, but it was shot through by a sharper\"},{\"text\":\"reek of sweat, which--one knew this at the first sniff, though it was\"},{\"text\":\"hard to say how--was the sweat of some person not present at the moment.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"In another room someone with a comb and a piece of toilet paper was\"},{\"text\":\"trying to keep tune with the military music which was still issuing\"},{\"text\":\"from the telescreen.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"half-apprehensive glance\"},{\"text\":\"at the door. 'They haven't been out today. And of course----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"She had a habit of breaking off her sentences in the middle. The kitchen\"}]","[{\"text\":\"water which smelt\"},{\"text\":\"worse than ever of cabbage. Winston knelt down and examined the angle-joint\"},{\"text\":\"of the pipe. He hated using his hands, and he hated bending down, which was\"},{\"text\":\"always liable to start him coughing. Mrs Parsons looked on helplessly.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Of course if Tom was home he'd put it right in a moment,' she said.\"},{\"text\":\"'He loves anything like that. He's ever so good with his hands, Tom is.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Parsons was Winston's fellow-employee at the Ministry of Truth. He was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"active man of paralysing stupidity, a mass of imbecile\"},{\"text\":\"enthusiasms--one of those completely unquestioning, devoted drudges on\"},{\"text\":\"whom, more even than on the Thought Police, the stability of the Party\"}]","[{\"text\":\"evicted from the\"},{\"text\":\"Youth League, and before graduating into the Youth League he had managed to\"},{\"text\":\"stay on in the Spies for a year beyond the statutory age. At the Ministry\"},{\"text\":\"he was employed in some subordinate post for which intelligence was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the other hand he was a leading figure on the Sports\"},{\"text\":\"Committee and all the other committees engaged in organizing community\"},{\"text\":\"hikes, spontaneous demonstrations, savings campaigns, and voluntary\"}]","[{\"text\":\"pride, between whiffs\"},{\"text\":\"of his pipe, that he had put in an appearance at the Community Centre every\"},{\"text\":\"evening for the past four years. An overpowering smell of sweat, a sort of\"},{\"text\":\"unconscious testimony to the strenuousness of his life, followed him about\"}]","[{\"text\":\"wherever he went, and even remained behind him after he had gone.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Have you got a spanner?' said Winston, fiddling with the nut on the\"},{\"text\":\"angle-joint.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"invertebrate. 'I don't\"},{\"text\":\"know, I'm sure. Perhaps the children----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"There was a trampling of boots and another blast on the comb as the\"},{\"text\":\"children charged into the living-room. Mrs Parsons brought the spanner.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston let out the water and disgustedly removed the clot of human hair\"},{\"text\":\"that had blocked up the pipe. He cleaned his fingers as best he could in\"},{\"text\":\"the cold water from the tap and went back into the other room.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hands!' yelled a savage voice.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"A handsome, tough-looking boy of nine had popped up from behind the table\"},{\"text\":\"and was menacing him with a toy automatic pistol, while his small sister,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"fragment of wood.\"},{\"text\":\"Both of them were dressed in the blue shorts, grey shirts, and red\"},{\"text\":\"neckerchiefs which were the uniform of the Spies. Winston raised