 She got two other girls to go with her, slipped off\"},{\"text\":\"from the hike, and spent the whole afternoon following a strange man. They\"},{\"text\":\"kept on his tail for two hours, right through the woods, and then, when\"}]","[{\"text\":\"they got into Amersham, handed him over to the patrols.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What did they do that for?' said Winston, somewhat taken aback. Parsons\"},{\"text\":\"went on triumphantly:\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"have been dropped\"},{\"text\":\"by parachute, for instance. But here's the point, old boy. What do you\"},{\"text\":\"think put her on to him in the first place? She spotted he was wearing a\"},{\"text\":\"funny kind of shoes--said she'd never seen anyone wearing shoes like that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"chances were he was a foreigner. Pretty smart for a nipper\"},{\"text\":\"of seven, eh?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What happened to the man?' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Ah, that I couldn't say, of course. But I wouldn't be altogether surprised\"}]","[{\"text\":\"if----' Parsons made the motion of aiming a rifle, and clicked his tongue\"},{\"text\":\"for the explosion.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Good,' said Syme abstractedly, without looking up from his strip of paper.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston dutifully.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What I mean to say, there is a war on,' said Parsons.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"As though in confirmation of this, a trumpet call floated from the\"},{\"text\":\"telescreen just above their heads. However, it was not the proclamation of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a military victory this time, but merely an announcement from the Ministry\"},{\"text\":\"of Plenty.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Comrades!' cried an eager youthful voice. 'Attention, comrades! We have\"},{\"text\":\"glorious news for you. We have won the battle for production! Returns now\"}]","[{\"text\":\"completed of the output of all classes of consumption goods show that the\"},{\"text\":\"standard of living has risen by no less than 20 per cent over the past\"},{\"text\":\"year. All over Oceania this morning there were irrepressible spontaneous\"}]","[{\"text\":\"out of factories and offices and\"},{\"text\":\"paraded through the streets with banners voicing their gratitude to Big\"},{\"text\":\"Brother for the new, happy life which his wise leadership has bestowed\"},{\"text\":\"upon us. Here are some of the completed figures. Foodstuffs----'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The phrase 'our new, happy life' recurred several times. It had been a\"},{\"text\":\"favourite of late with the Ministry of Plenty. Parsons, his attention\"},{\"text\":\"caught by the trumpet call, sat listening with a sort of gaping solemnity,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"not follow the figures, but he was\"},{\"text\":\"aware that they were in some way a cause for satisfaction. He had lugged\"},{\"text\":\"out a huge and filthy pipe which was already half full of charred tobacco.\"},{\"text\":\"With the tobacco ration at 100 grammes a week it was seldom possible to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"fill a pipe to the top. Winston was smoking a Victory Cigarette which he\"},{\"text\":\"held carefully horizontal. The new ration did not start till tomorrow and\"},{\"text\":\"he had only four cigarettes left. For the moment he had shut his ears to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to the stuff that streamed out of the\"},{\"text\":\"telescreen. It appeared that there had even been demonstrations to thank\"},{\"text\":\"Big Brother for raising the chocolate ration to twenty grammes a week. And\"},{\"text\":\"only yesterday, he reflected, it had been announced that the ration was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to be REDUCED to twenty grammes a week. Was it possible that they could\"},{\"text\":\"swallow that, after only twenty-four hours? Yes, they swallowed it. Parsons\"},{\"text\":\"swallowed it easily, with the stupidity of an animal. The eyeless creature\"}]","[{\"text\":\"fanatically, passionately, with a furious\"},{\"text\":\"desire to track down, denounce, and vaporize anyone who should suggest that\"},{\"text\":\"last week the ration had been thirty grammes. Syme, too--in some more\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Was he, then, ALONE\"},{\"text\":\"in the possession of a memory?\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The fabulous statistics continued to pour out of the telescreen. As\"},{\"text\":\"compared with last year there was more food, more clothes, more houses,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"more cooking-pots, more fuel, more ships, more helicopters,\"},{\"text\":\"more books, more babies--more of everything except disease, crime, and\"},{\"text\":\"insanity. Year by year and minute by minute, everybody and everything was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"done earlier Winston had taken up\"},{\"text\":\"his spoon and was dabbling in the pale-coloured gravy that dribbled across\"},{\"text\":\"the table, drawing a long streak of it out into a pattern. He meditated\"},{\"text\":\"resentfully on the physical texture of life. Had it always been like\"}]","[{\"text\":\"this? Had food always tasted like this? He looked round the canteen.\"},{\"text\":\"A low-ceilinged, crowded room, its walls grimy from the contact of\"},{\"text\":\"innumerable bodies; battered metal tables and chairs, placed so close\"}]","[{\"text\":\"touching; bent spoons, dented trays,\"},{\"text\":\"coarse white mugs; all surfaces greasy, grime in every crack; and a\"},{\"text\":\"sourish, composite smell of bad gin and bad coffee and metallic stew and\"},{\"text\":\"dirty clothes. Always in your stomach and in your skin there was a sort\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of protest, a feeling that you had been cheated of something that you had\"},{\"text\":\"a right to. It was true that he had no memories of anything greatly\"},{\"text\":\"different. In any time that he could accurately remember, there had never\"}]","[{\"text\":\"never had socks or underclothes that\"},{\"text\":\"were not full of holes, furniture had always been battered and rickety,\"},{\"text\":\"rooms underheated, tube trains crowded, houses falling to pieces,\"},{\"text\":\"bread dark-coloured, tea a rarity, coffee filthy-tasting, cigarettes\"}]","[{\"text\":\"insufficient--nothing cheap and plentiful except synthetic gin. And though,\"},{\"text\":\"of course, it grew worse as one's body aged, was it not a sign that this\"},{\"text\":\"was NOT the natural order of things, if one's heart sickened at the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"interminable winters, the stickiness\"},{\"text\":\"of one's socks, the lifts that never worked, the cold water, the gritty\"},{\"text\":\"soap, the cigarettes that came to pieces, the food with its strange evil\"},{\"text\":\"tastes? Why should one feel it to be intolerable unless one had some kind\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of ancestral memory that things had once been different?\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He looked round the canteen again. Nearly everyone was ugly, and would\"},{\"text\":\"still have been ugly even if dressed otherwise than in the uniform blue\"}]","[{\"text\":\"room, sitting at a table alone, a small,\"},{\"text\":\"curiously beetle-like man was drinking a cup of coffee, his little eyes\"},{\"text\":\"darting suspicious glances from side to side. How easy it was, thought\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the physical type\"},{\"text\":\"set up by the Party as an ideal--tall muscular youths and deep-bosomed\"},{\"text\":\"maidens, blond-haired, vital, sunburnt, carefree--existed and even\"},{\"text\":\"predominated. Actually, so far as he could judge, the majority of people\"}]","[{\"text\":\"were small, dark, and ill-favoured. It was curious how that\"},{\"text\":\"beetle-like type proliferated in the Ministries: little dumpy men, growing\"},{\"text\":\"stout very early in life, with short legs, swift scuttling movements, and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"eyes. It was the type that seemed to\"},{\"text\":\"flourish best under the dominion of the Party.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The announcement from the Ministry of Plenty ended on another trumpet call\"},{\"text\":\"and gave way to tinny music. Parsons, stirred to vague enthusiasm by the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"bombardment of figures, took his pipe out of his mouth.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'The Ministry of Plenty's certainly done a good job this year,' he said\"},{\"text\":\"with a knowing shake of his head. 'By the way, Smith old boy, I suppose\"}]","[{\"text\":\"can let me have?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Not one,' said Winston. 'I've been using the same blade for six weeks\"},{\"text\":\"myself.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Ah, well--just thought I'd ask you, old boy.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Sorry,' said Winston.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The quacking voice from the next table, temporarily silenced during the\"},{\"text\":\"Ministry's announcement, had started up again, as loud as ever. For some\"},{\"text\":\"reason Winston suddenly found himself thinking of Mrs Parsons, with her\"}]","[{\"text\":\"creases of her face. Within two years those\"},{\"text\":\"children would be denouncing her to the Thought Police. Mrs Parsons would\"},{\"text\":\"be vaporized. Syme would be vaporized. Winston would be vaporized. O'Brien\"}]","[{\"text\":\"never be vaporized.\"},{\"text\":\"The eyeless creature with the quacking voice would never be vaporized.\"},{\"text\":\"The little beetle-like men who scuttle so nimbly through the labyrinthine\"},{\"text\":\"corridors of Ministries they, too, would never be vaporized. And the girl\"}]","[{\"text\":\"with dark hair, the girl from the Fiction Department--she would never be\"},{\"text\":\"vaporized either. It seemed to him that he knew instinctively who would\"},{\"text\":\"survive and who would perish: though just what it was that made for\"},{\"text\":\"survival, it was not easy to say.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"At this moment he was dragged out of his reverie with a violent jerk. The\"},{\"text\":\"girl at the next table had turned partly round and was looking at him. It\"},{\"text\":\"was the girl with dark hair. She was looking at him in a sidelong way, but\"}]","[{\"text\":\"she caught his eye she looked away\"},{\"text\":\"again.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The sweat started out on Winston's backbone. A horrible pang of terror\"},{\"text\":\"went through him. It was gone almost at once, but it left a sort of nagging\"}]","[{\"text\":\"watching him? Why did she keep following him\"},{\"text\":\"about? Unfortunately he could not remember whether she had already been at\"},{\"text\":\"the table when he arrived, or had come there afterwards. But yesterday, at\"}]","[{\"text\":\"immediately behind him\"},{\"text\":\"when there was no apparent need to do so. Quite likely her real object had\"},{\"text\":\"been to listen to him and make sure whether he was shouting loudly enough.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"not actually a member\"},{\"text\":\"of the Thought Police, but then it was precisely the amateur spy who was\"},{\"text\":\"the greatest danger of all. He did not know how long she had been looking\"},{\"text\":\"at him, but perhaps for as much as five minutes, and it was possible\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that his features had not been perfectly under control. It was terribly\"},{\"text\":\"dangerous to let your thoughts wander when you were in any public place\"},{\"text\":\"or within range of a telescreen. The smallest thing could give you away.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"anxiety, a habit of muttering to\"},{\"text\":\"yourself--anything that carried with it the suggestion of abnormality, of\"},{\"text\":\"having something to hide. In any case, to wear an improper expression on\"},{\"text\":\"your face (to look incredulous when a victory was announced, for example)\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was itself a punishable offence. There was even a word for it in Newspeak:\"},{\"text\":\"FACECRIME, it was called.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The girl had turned her back on him again. Perhaps after all she was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that she had sat so\"},{\"text\":\"close to him two days running. His cigarette had gone out, and he laid it\"},{\"text\":\"carefully on the edge of the table. He would finish smoking it after work,\"},{\"text\":\"if he could keep the tobacco in it. Quite likely the person at the next\"}]","[{\"text\":\"table was a spy of the Thought Police, and quite likely he would be in the\"},{\"text\":\"cellars of the Ministry of Love within three days, but a cigarette end\"},{\"text\":\"must not be wasted. Syme had folded up his strip of paper and stowed it\"}]","[{\"text\":\"talking again.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Did I ever tell you, old boy,' he said, chuckling round the stem of his\"},{\"text\":\"pipe, 'about the time when those two nippers of mine set fire to the old\"},{\"text\":\"market-woman's skirt because they saw her wrapping up sausages in a poster\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of B.B.? Sneaked up behind her and set fire to it with a box of matches.\"},{\"text\":\"Burned her quite badly, I believe. Little beggars, eh? But keen as mustard!\"},{\"text\":\"That's a first-rate training they give them in the Spies nowadays--better\"}]","[{\"text\":\"think's the latest thing they've served\"},{\"text\":\"them out with? Ear trumpets for listening through keyholes! My little\"},{\"text\":\"girl brought one home the other night--tried it out on our sitting-room\"}]","[{\"text\":\"her ear to the\"},{\"text\":\"hole. Of course it's only a toy, mind you. Still, gives 'em the right\"},{\"text\":\"idea, eh?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"At this moment the telescreen let out a piercing whistle. It was the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"feet to join in\"},{\"text\":\"the struggle round the lifts, and the remaining tobacco fell out of\"},{\"text\":\"Winston's cigarette.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Chapter 6\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston was writing in his diary:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"It was three years ago. It was on a dark evening, in a narrow\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was standing near a\"},{\"text\":\"doorway in the wall, under a street lamp that hardly gave any light. She\"},{\"text\":\"had a young face, painted very thick. It was really the paint that appealed\"},{\"text\":\"to me, the whiteness of it, like a mask, and the bright red lips. Party\"}]","[{\"text\":\"women never paint their faces. There was nobody else in the street, and no\"},{\"text\":\"telescreens. She said two dollars. I----\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"For the moment it was too difficult to go on. He shut his eyes and pressed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"against them, trying to squeeze out the vision that kept\"},{\"text\":\"recurring. He had an almost overwhelming temptation to shout a string of\"},{\"text\":\"filthy words at the top of his voice. Or to bang his head against the wall,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"window--to do any\"},{\"text\":\"violent or noisy or painful thing that might black out the memory that was\"},{\"text\":\"tormenting him.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Your worst enemy, he reflected, was your own nervous system. At any moment\"}]","[{\"text\":\"into some visible\"},{\"text\":\"symptom. He thought of a man whom he had passed in the street a few weeks\"},{\"text\":\"back; a quite ordinary-looking man, a Party member, aged thirty-five to\"},{\"text\":\"forty, tallish and thin, carrying a brief-case. They were a few metres\"}]","[{\"text\":\"left side of the man's face was suddenly contorted by a sort\"},{\"text\":\"of spasm. It happened again just as they were passing one another: it was\"},{\"text\":\"only a twitch, a quiver, rapid as the clicking of a camera shutter, but\"}]","[{\"text\":\"thinking at the time: That poor devil is\"},{\"text\":\"done for. And what was frightening was that the action was quite possibly\"},{\"text\":\"unconscious. The most deadly danger of all was talking in your sleep. There\"}]","[{\"text\":\"see.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He drew his breath and went on writing:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"I went with her through the doorway and across a backyard into a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"basement kitchen. There was a bed against the wall, and a lamp on the\"},{\"text\":\"table, turned down very low. She----\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"His teeth were set on edge. He would have liked to spit. Simultaneously\"}]","[{\"text\":\"kitchen he thought of Katharine, his wife.\"},{\"text\":\"Winston was married--had been married, at any rate: probably he still was\"},{\"text\":\"married, so far as he knew his wife was not dead. He seemed to breathe\"}]","[{\"text\":\"odour compounded\"},{\"text\":\"of bugs and dirty clothes and villainous cheap scent, but nevertheless\"},{\"text\":\"alluring, because no woman of the Party ever used scent, or could be\"},{\"text\":\"imagined as doing so. Only the proles used scent. In his mind the smell\"}]","[{\"text\":\"inextricably mixed up with fornication.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"When he had gone with that woman it had been his first lapse in two years\"},{\"text\":\"or thereabouts. Consorting with prostitutes was forbidden, of course, but\"}]","[{\"text\":\"could occasionally nerve yourself to\"},{\"text\":\"break. It was dangerous, but it was not a life-and-death matter. To be\"},{\"text\":\"caught with a prostitute might mean five years in a forced-labour camp:\"},{\"text\":\"not more, if you had committed no other offence. And it was easy enough,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"provided that you could avoid being caught in the act. The poorer quarters\"},{\"text\":\"swarmed with women who were ready to sell themselves. Some could even be\"},{\"text\":\"purchased for a bottle of gin, which the proles were not supposed to drink.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to encourage prostitution, as an outlet\"},{\"text\":\"for instincts which could not be altogether suppressed. Mere debauchery\"},{\"text\":\"did not matter very much, so long as it was furtive and joyless and only\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The unforgivable\"},{\"text\":\"crime was promiscuity between Party members. But--though this was one\"},{\"text\":\"of the crimes that the accused in the great purges invariably confessed\"},{\"text\":\"to--it was difficult to imagine any such thing actually happening.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The aim of the Party was not merely to prevent men and women from forming\"},{\"text\":\"loyalties which it might not be able to control. Its real, undeclared\"},{\"text\":\"purpose was to remove all pleasure from the sexual act. Not love so much\"}]","[{\"text\":\"marriage as well as outside it. All\"},{\"text\":\"marriages between Party members had to be approved by a committee\"},{\"text\":\"appointed for the purpose, and--though the principle was never clearly\"},{\"text\":\"stated--permission was always refused if the couple concerned gave\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the impression of being physically attracted to one another. The only\"},{\"text\":\"recognized purpose of marriage was to beget children for the service of\"},{\"text\":\"the Party. Sexual intercourse was to be looked on as a slightly disgusting\"}]","[{\"text\":\"enema. This again was never put into plain\"},{\"text\":\"words, but in an indirect way it was rubbed into every Party member from\"},{\"text\":\"childhood onwards. There were even organizations such as the Junior\"}]","[{\"text\":\"both sexes. All\"},{\"text\":\"children were to be begotten by artificial insemination (ARTSEM, it was\"},{\"text\":\"called in Newspeak) and brought up in public institutions. This, Winston\"},{\"text\":\"was aware, was not meant altogether seriously, but somehow it fitted in\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ideology of the Party. The Party was trying to kill the\"},{\"text\":\"sex instinct, or, if it could not be killed, then to distort it and dirty\"},{\"text\":\"it. He did not know why this was so, but it seemed natural that it should\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Party's efforts were\"},{\"text\":\"largely successful.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He thought again of Katharine. It must be nine, ten--nearly eleven years\"},{\"text\":\"since they had parted. It was curious how seldom he thought of her. For\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was capable of forgetting that he had ever been married.\"},{\"text\":\"They had only been together for about fifteen months. The Party did not\"},{\"text\":\"permit divorce, but it rather encouraged separation in cases where there\"},{\"text\":\"were no children.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"tall, fair-haired girl, very straight, with splendid\"},{\"text\":\"movements. She had a bold, aquiline face, a face that one might have called\"},{\"text\":\"noble until one discovered that there was as nearly as possible nothing\"}]","[{\"text\":\"decided--though perhaps\"},{\"text\":\"it was only that he knew her more intimately than he knew most people--that\"},{\"text\":\"she had without exception the most stupid, vulgar, empty mind that he had\"},{\"text\":\"ever encountered. She had not a thought in her head that was not a slogan,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and there was no imbecility, absolutely none that she was not capable of\"},{\"text\":\"swallowing if the Party handed it out to her. 'The human sound-track' he\"},{\"text\":\"nicknamed her in his own mind. Yet he could have endured living with her\"}]","[{\"text\":\"thing--sex.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"As soon as he touched her she seemed to wince and stiffen. To embrace her\"},{\"text\":\"was like embracing a jointed wooden image. And what was strange was that\"},{\"text\":\"even when she was clasping him against her he had the feeling that she\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was simultaneously pushing him away with all her strength. The rigidity\"},{\"text\":\"of her muscles managed to convey that impression. She would lie there\"},{\"text\":\"with shut eyes, neither resisting nor co-operating but SUBMITTING. It was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"after a while, horrible. But even then\"},{\"text\":\"he could have borne living with her if it had been agreed that they should\"},{\"text\":\"remain celibate. But curiously enough it was Katharine who refused this.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the performance\"},{\"text\":\"continued to happen, once a week quite regularly, whenever it was not\"},{\"text\":\"impossible. She even used to remind him of it in the morning, as something\"},{\"text\":\"which had to be done that evening and which must not be forgotten. She had\"}]","[{\"text\":\"One was 'making a baby', and the other was 'our duty to\"},{\"text\":\"the Party' (yes, she had actually used that phrase). Quite soon he grew to\"},{\"text\":\"have a feeling of positive dread when the appointed day came round. But\"}]","[{\"text\":\"give up trying,\"},{\"text\":\"and soon afterwards they parted.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston sighed inaudibly. He picked up his pen again and\"},{\"text\":\"wrote:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"down on the bed, and at once, without any kind of\"},{\"text\":\"preliminary in the most coarse, horrible way you can imagine, pulled up\"},{\"text\":\"her skirt. I----\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He saw himself standing there in the dim lamplight, with the smell of bugs\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and cheap scent in his nostrils, and in his heart a feeling of defeat and\"},{\"text\":\"resentment which even at that moment was mixed up with the thought of\"},{\"text\":\"Katharine's white body, frozen for ever by the hypnotic power of the Party.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"this? Why could he not have a woman of\"},{\"text\":\"his own instead of these filthy scuffles at intervals of years? But a real\"},{\"text\":\"love affair was an almost unthinkable event. The women of the Party were\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Party loyalty. By\"},{\"text\":\"careful early conditioning, by games and cold water, by the rubbish that\"},{\"text\":\"was dinned into them at school and in the Spies and the Youth League, by\"},{\"text\":\"lectures, parades, songs, slogans, and martial music, the natural feeling\"}]","[{\"text\":\"out of them. His reason told him that there must be\"},{\"text\":\"exceptions, but his heart did not believe it. They were all impregnable,\"},{\"text\":\"as the Party intended that they should be. And what he wanted, more even\"}]","[{\"text\":\"even if it were\"},{\"text\":\"only once in his whole life. The sexual act, successfully performed, was\"},{\"text\":\"rebellion. Desire was thoughtcrime. Even to have awakened Katharine, if he\"},{\"text\":\"could have achieved it, would have been like a seduction, although she was\"},{\"text\":\"his wife.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"But the rest of the story had got to be written down. He wrote:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"I turned up the lamp. When I saw her in the light----\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"After the darkness the feeble light of the paraffin lamp had seemed very\"},{\"text\":\"bright. For the first time he could see the woman properly. He had taken a\"},{\"text\":\"step towards her and then halted, full of lust and terror. He was painfully\"}]","[{\"text\":\"coming here. It was perfectly\"},{\"text\":\"possible that the patrols would catch him on the way out: for that matter\"},{\"text\":\"they might be waiting outside the door at this moment. If he went away\"},{\"text\":\"without even doing what he had come here to do----!\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"It had got to be written down, it had got to be confessed. What he had\"},{\"text\":\"suddenly seen in the lamplight was that the woman was OLD. The paint was\"},{\"text\":\"plastered so thick on her face that it looked as though it might crack\"}]","[{\"text\":\"streaks of white in her hair; but the\"},{\"text\":\"truly dreadful detail was that her mouth had fallen a little open,\"},{\"text\":\"revealing nothing except a cavernous blackness. She had no teeth at all.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He wrote hurriedly, in scrabbling handwriting:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"When I saw her in the light she was quite an old woman, fifty years old\"},{\"text\":\"at least. But I went ahead and did it just the same.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He pressed his fingers against his eyelids again. He had written it down\"}]","[{\"text\":\"made no difference. The therapy had not worked. The urge\"},{\"text\":\"to shout filthy words at the top of his voice was as strong as ever.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Chapter 7\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'If there is hope,' wrote Winston, 'it lies in the proles.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"If there was hope, it MUST lie in the proles, because only there in those\"},{\"text\":\"swarming disregarded masses, 85 per cent of the population of Oceania,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"destroy the Party ever be generated. The Party could\"},{\"text\":\"not be overthrown from within. Its enemies, if it had any enemies, had\"},{\"text\":\"no way of coming together or even of identifying one another. Even if\"}]","[{\"text\":\"might, it was\"},{\"text\":\"inconceivable that its members could ever assemble in larger numbers than\"},{\"text\":\"twos and threes. Rebellion meant a look in the eyes, an inflexion of the\"},{\"text\":\"voice, at the most, an occasional whispered word. But the proles, if only\"}]","[{\"text\":\"become conscious of their own strength. would have no\"},{\"text\":\"need to conspire. They needed only to rise up and shake themselves like\"},{\"text\":\"a horse shaking off flies. If they chose they could blow the Party to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"occur to them to\"},{\"text\":\"do it? And yet----!\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He remembered how once he had been walking down a crowded street when a\"},{\"text\":\"tremendous shout of hundreds of voices women's voices--had burst from a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was a great formidable cry of anger\"},{\"text\":\"and despair, a deep, loud 'Oh-o-o-o-oh!' that went humming on like the\"},{\"text\":\"reverberation of a bell. His heart had leapt. It's started! he had thought.\"},{\"text\":\"A riot! The proles are breaking loose at last! When he had reached the spot\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it was to see a mob of two or three hundred women crowding round the stalls\"},{\"text\":\"of a street market, with faces as tragic as though they had been the doomed\"},{\"text\":\"passengers on a sinking ship. But at this moment the general despair broke\"}]","[{\"text\":\"quarrels. It appeared that one of the\"},{\"text\":\"stalls had been selling tin saucepans. They were wretched, flimsy things,\"},{\"text\":\"but cooking-pots of any kind were always difficult to get. Now the supply\"},{\"text\":\"had unexpectedly given out. The successful women, bumped and jostled by\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the rest, were trying to make off with their saucepans while dozens of\"},{\"text\":\"others clamoured round the stall, accusing the stall-keeper of favouritism\"},{\"text\":\"and of having more saucepans somewhere in reserve. There was a fresh\"}]","[{\"text\":\"one of them with her hair coming\"},{\"text\":\"down, had got hold of the same saucepan and were trying to tear it out of\"},{\"text\":\"one another's hands. For a moment they were both tugging, and then the\"},{\"text\":\"handle came off. Winston watched them disgustedly. And yet, just for a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"moment, what almost frightening power had sounded in that cry from only\"},{\"text\":\"a few hundred throats! Why was it that they could never shout like that\"},{\"text\":\"about anything that mattered?\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He wrote:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Until they become conscious they will never rebel, and until after they\"},{\"text\":\"have rebelled they cannot become conscious.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"That, he reflected, might almost have been a transcription from one of the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The Party claimed, of course, to have liberated the proles\"},{\"text\":\"from bondage. Before the Revolution they had been hideously oppressed by\"},{\"text\":\"the capitalists, they had been starved and flogged, women had been forced\"}]","[{\"text\":\"still did work in the coal mines, as a\"},{\"text\":\"matter of fact), children had been sold into the factories at the age\"},{\"text\":\"of six. But simultaneously, true to the Principles of doublethink, the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"must be kept in\"},{\"text\":\"subjection, like animals, by the application of a few simple rules. In\"},{\"text\":\"reality very little was known about the proles. It was not necessary to\"},{\"text\":\"know much. So long as they continued to work and breed, their other\"}]","[{\"text\":\"without importance. Left to themselves, like cattle turned\"},{\"text\":\"loose upon the plains of Argentina, they had reverted to a style of life\"},{\"text\":\"that appeared to be natural to them, a sort of ancestral pattern. They were\"}]","[{\"text\":\"they went to work at twelve, they passed\"},{\"text\":\"through a brief blossoming-period of beauty and sexual desire, they married\"},{\"text\":\"at twenty, they were middle-aged at thirty, they died, for the most part,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"children, petty\"},{\"text\":\"quarrels with neighbours, films, football, beer, and above all, gambling,\"},{\"text\":\"filled up the horizon of their minds. To keep them in control was not\"},{\"text\":\"difficult. A few agents of the Thought Police moved always among them,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"rumours and marking down and eliminating the few\"},{\"text\":\"individuals who were judged capable of becoming dangerous; but no attempt\"},{\"text\":\"was made to indoctrinate them with the ideology of the Party. It was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"feelings. All that\"},{\"text\":\"was required of them was a primitive patriotism which could be appealed to\"},{\"text\":\"whenever it was necessary to make them accept longer working-hours or\"},{\"text\":\"shorter rations. And even when they became discontented, as they sometimes\"}]","[{\"text\":\"discontent led nowhere, because being without general ideas,\"},{\"text\":\"they could only focus it on petty specific grievances. The larger evils\"},{\"text\":\"invariably escaped their notice. The great majority of proles did not even\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the civil police interfered with them\"},{\"text\":\"very little. There was a vast amount of criminality in London, a whole\"},{\"text\":\"world-within-a-world of thieves, bandits, prostitutes, drug-peddlers, and\"},{\"text\":\"racketeers of every description; but since it all happened among the proles\"}]","[{\"text\":\"themselves, it was of no importance. In all questions of morals they were\"},{\"text\":\"allowed to follow their ancestral code. The sexual puritanism of the\"},{\"text\":\"Party was not imposed upon them. Promiscuity went unpunished, divorce\"}]","[{\"text\":\"religious worship would have been\"},{\"text\":\"permitted if the proles had shown any sign of needing or wanting it.\"},{\"text\":\"They were beneath suspicion. As the Party slogan put it: 'Proles and\"},{\"text\":\"animals are free.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"scratched his varicose ulcer. It\"},{\"text\":\"had begun itching again. The thing you invariably came back to was the\"},{\"text\":\"impossibility of knowing what life before the Revolution had really been\"},{\"text\":\"like. He took out of the drawer a copy of a children's history textbook\"}]","[{\"text\":\"which he had borrowed from Mrs Parsons, and began copying a passage into\"},{\"text\":\"the diary:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"In the old days (it ran), before the glorious Revolution, London was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"not the beautiful city that we know today. It was a dark, dirty, miserable\"},{\"text\":\"place where hardly anybody had enough to eat and where hundreds and\"},{\"text\":\"thousands of poor people had no boots on their feet and not even a roof to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"you had to work twelve hours a day for\"},{\"text\":\"cruel masters who flogged them with whips if they worked too slowly and\"},{\"text\":\"fed them on nothing but stale breadcrusts and water. But in among all\"}]","[{\"text\":\"beautiful houses\"},{\"text\":\"that were lived in by rich men who had as many as thirty servants to look\"},{\"text\":\"after them. These rich men were called capitalists. They were fat, ugly\"},{\"text\":\"men with wicked faces, like the one in the picture on the opposite page.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"he is dressed in a long black coat which was called a\"},{\"text\":\"frock coat, and a queer, shiny hat shaped like a stovepipe, which was\"},{\"text\":\"called a top hat. This was the uniform of the capitalists, and no one else\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in the world, and\"},{\"text\":\"everyone else was their slave. They owned all the land, all the houses,\"},{\"text\":\"all the factories, and all the money. If anyone disobeyed them they could\"},{\"text\":\"throw them into prison, or they could take his job away and starve him to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ordinary person spoke to a capitalist he had to cringe and\"},{\"text\":\"bow to him, and take off his cap and address him as 'Sir'. The chief of\"},{\"text\":\"all the capitalists was called the King, and----\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"rest of the catalogue. There would be mention of the\"},{\"text\":\"bishops in their lawn sleeves, the judges in their ermine robes, the\"},{\"text\":\"pillory, the stocks, the treadmill, the cat-o'-nine tails, the Lord Mayor's\"}]","[{\"text\":\"There was also\"},{\"text\":\"something called the JUS PRIMAE NOCTIS, which would probably not be\"},{\"text\":\"mentioned in a textbook for children. It was the law by which every\"},{\"text\":\"capitalist had the right to sleep with any woman working in one of his\"},{\"text\":\"factories.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"How could you tell how much of it was lies? It MIGHT be true that the\"},{\"text\":\"average human being was better off now than he had been before the\"},{\"text\":\"Revolution. The only evidence to the contrary was the mute protest in your\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that the conditions you lived in were\"},{\"text\":\"intolerable and that at some other time they must have been different. It\"},{\"text\":\"struck him that the truly characteristic thing about modern life was not\"},{\"text\":\"its cruelty and insecurity, but simply its bareness, its dinginess, its\"}]","[{\"text\":\"listlessness. Life, if you looked about you, bore no resemblance not only\"},{\"text\":\"to the lies that streamed out of the telescreens, but even to the ideals\"},{\"text\":\"that the Party was trying to achieve. Great areas of it, even for a Party\"}]","[{\"text\":\"non-political, a matter of slogging through dreary\"},{\"text\":\"jobs, fighting for a place on the Tube, darning a worn-out sock, cadging\"},{\"text\":\"a saccharine tablet, saving a cigarette end. The ideal set up by the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"world of steel\"},{\"text\":\"and concrete, of monstrous machines and terrifying weapons--a nation of\"},{\"text\":\"warriors and fanatics, marching forward in perfect unity, all thinking the\"},{\"text\":\"same thoughts and shouting the same slogans, perpetually working, fighting,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"persecuting--three hundred million people all with the same\"},{\"text\":\"face. The reality was decaying, dingy cities where underfed people shuffled\"},{\"text\":\"to and fro in leaky shoes, in patched-up nineteenth-century houses that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"lavatories. He seemed to see a vision of\"},{\"text\":\"London, vast and ruinous, city of a million dustbins, and mixed up with it\"},{\"text\":\"was a picture of Mrs Parsons, a woman with lined face and wispy hair,\"},{\"text\":\"fiddling helplessly with a blocked waste-pipe.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"He reached down and scratched his ankle again. Day and night the\"},{\"text\":\"telescreens bruised your ears with statistics proving that people today\"},{\"text\":\"had more food, more clothes, better houses, better recreations--that they\"}]","[{\"text\":\"were bigger, healthier, stronger,\"},{\"text\":\"happier, more intelligent, better educated, than the people of fifty years\"},{\"text\":\"ago. Not a word of it could ever be proved or disproved. The Party claimed,\"},{\"text\":\"for example, that today 40 per cent of adult proles were literate: before\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the Revolution, it was said, the number had only been 15 per cent. The\"},{\"text\":\"Party claimed that the infant mortality rate was now only 160 per\"},{\"text\":\"thousand, whereas before the Revolution it had been 300--and so it went\"}]","[{\"text\":\"with two unknowns. It might very well be\"},{\"text\":\"that literally every word in the history books, even the things that one\"},{\"text\":\"accepted without question, was pure fantasy. For all he knew there might\"}]","[{\"text\":\"or any such creature\"},{\"text\":\"as a capitalist, or any such garment as a top hat.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Everything faded into mist. The past was erased, the erasure was forgotten,\"},{\"text\":\"the lie became truth. Just once in his life he had possessed--AFTER the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"event: that was what counted--concrete, unmistakable evidence of an act of\"},{\"text\":\"falsification. He had held it between his fingers for as long as thirty\"},{\"text\":\"seconds. In 1973, it must have been--at any rate, it was at about the time\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the really relevant date was seven\"},{\"text\":\"or eight years earlier.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The story really began in the middle sixties, the period of the great\"},{\"text\":\"purges in which the original leaders of the Revolution were wiped out\"}]","[{\"text\":\"By 1970 none of them was left, except Big Brother\"},{\"text\":\"himself. All the rest had by that time been exposed as traitors and\"},{\"text\":\"counter-revolutionaries. Goldstein had fled and was hiding no one knew\"}]","[{\"text\":\"while the majority\"},{\"text\":\"had been executed after spectacular public trials at which they made\"},{\"text\":\"confession of their crimes. Among the last survivors were three men named\"},{\"text\":\"Jones, Aaronson, and Rutherford. It must have been in 1965 that these three\"}]","[{\"text\":\"As often happened, they had vanished for a year or more,\"},{\"text\":\"so that one did not know whether they were alive or dead, and then had\"},{\"text\":\"suddenly been brought forth to incriminate themselves in the usual way.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that date, too, the\"},{\"text\":\"enemy was Eurasia), embezzlement of public funds, the murder of various\"},{\"text\":\"trusted Party members, intrigues against the leadership of Big Brother\"},{\"text\":\"which had started long before the Revolution happened, and acts of sabotage\"}]","[{\"text\":\"causing the death of hundreds of thousands of people. After confessing to\"},{\"text\":\"these things they had been pardoned, reinstated in the Party, and given\"},{\"text\":\"posts which were in fact sinecures but which sounded important. All three\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'The Times', analysing the reasons\"},{\"text\":\"for their defection and promising to make amends.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Some time after their release Winston had actually seen all three of them\"},{\"text\":\"in the Chestnut Tree Cafe. He remembered the sort of terrified fascination\"}]","[{\"text\":\"with which he had watched them out of the corner of his eye. They were men\"},{\"text\":\"far older than himself, relics of the ancient world, almost the last great\"},{\"text\":\"figures left over from the heroic days of the Party. The glamour of the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"war still faintly clung to them. He had\"},{\"text\":\"the feeling, though already at that time facts and dates were growing\"},{\"text\":\"blurry, that he had known their names years earlier than he had known that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"untouchables, doomed\"},{\"text\":\"with absolute certainty to extinction within a year or two. No one who had\"},{\"text\":\"once fallen into the hands of the Thought Police ever escaped in the end.\"},{\"text\":\"They were corpses waiting to be sent back to the grave.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"There was no one at any of the tables nearest to them. It was not wise\"},{\"text\":\"even to be seen in the neighbourhood of such people. They were sitting\"},{\"text\":\"in silence before glasses of the gin flavoured with cloves which was the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it was Rutherford whose appearance\"},{\"text\":\"had most impressed Winston. Rutherford had once been a famous caricaturist,\"},{\"text\":\"whose brutal cartoons had helped to inflame popular opinion before and\"},{\"text\":\"during the Revolution. Even now, at long intervals, his cartoons were\"}]","[{\"text\":\"appearing in The Times. They were simply an imitation of his earlier\"},{\"text\":\"manner, and curiously lifeless and unconvincing. Always they were a\"},{\"text\":\"rehashing of the ancient themes--slum tenements, starving children, street\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hats--even on the barricades the capitalists\"},{\"text\":\"still seemed to cling to their top hats an endless, hopeless effort to\"},{\"text\":\"get back into the past. He was a monstrous man, with a mane of greasy\"}]","[{\"text\":\"negroid lips. At one\"},{\"text\":\"time he must have been immensely strong; now his great body was sagging,\"},{\"text\":\"sloping, bulging, falling away in every direction. He seemed to be breaking\"},{\"text\":\"up before one's eyes, like a mountain crumbling.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"It was the lonely hour of fifteen. Winston could not now remember how he\"},{\"text\":\"had come to be in the cafe at such a time. The place was almost empty. A\"},{\"text\":\"tinny music was trickling from the telescreens. The three men sat in their\"}]","[{\"text\":\"speaking. Uncommanded, the waiter brought\"},{\"text\":\"fresh glasses of gin. There was a chessboard on the table beside them, with\"},{\"text\":\"the pieces set out but no game started. And then, for perhaps half a minute\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that they were\"},{\"text\":\"playing changed, and the tone of the music changed too. There came into\"},{\"text\":\"it--but it was something hard to describe. It was a peculiar, cracked,\"},{\"text\":\"braying, jeering note: in his mind Winston called it a yellow note. And\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the telescreen was singing:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Under the spreading chestnut tree\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"I sold you and you sold me:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"There lie they, and here lie we\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"nder the spreading chestnut tree.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The three men never stirred. But when Winston glanced again at Rutherford's\"}]","[{\"text\":\"saw that his eyes were full of tears. And for the first\"},{\"text\":\"time he noticed, with a kind of inward shudder, and yet not knowing\"},{\"text\":\"AT WHAT he shuddered, that both Aaronson and Rutherford had broken noses.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"re-arrested. It appeared that they had\"},{\"text\":\"engaged in fresh conspiracies from the very moment of their release. At\"},{\"text\":\"their second trial they confessed to all their old crimes over again, with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"their fate was recorded\"},{\"text\":\"in the Party histories, a warning to posterity. About five years after\"},{\"text\":\"this, in 1973, Winston was unrolling a wad of documents which had just\"},{\"text\":\"flopped out of the pneumatic tube on to his desk when he came on a fragment\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of paper which had evidently been slipped in among the others and then\"},{\"text\":\"forgotten. The instant he had flattened it out he saw its significance.\"},{\"text\":\"It was a half-page torn out of 'The Times' of about ten years earlier--the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"included the date--and it contained a\"},{\"text\":\"photograph of the delegates at some Party function in New York. Prominent\"},{\"text\":\"in the middle of the group were Jones, Aaronson, and Rutherford. There was\"},{\"text\":\"no mistaking them, in any case their names were in the caption at the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"bottom.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The point was that at both trials all three men had confessed that on that\"},{\"text\":\"date they had been on Eurasian soil. They had flown from a secret airfield\"},{\"text\":\"in Canada to a rendezvous somewhere in Siberia, and had conferred with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"members of the Eurasian General Staff, to whom they had betrayed important\"},{\"text\":\"military secrets. The date had stuck in Winston's memory because it chanced\"},{\"text\":\"to be midsummer day; but the whole story must be on record in countless\"}]","[{\"text\":\"one possible conclusion: the\"},{\"text\":\"confessions were lies.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Of course, this was not in itself a discovery. Even at that time Winston\"},{\"text\":\"had not imagined that the people who were wiped out in the purges had\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the crimes that they were accused of. But this was\"},{\"text\":\"concrete evidence; it was a fragment of the abolished past, like a fossil\"},{\"text\":\"bone which turns up in the wrong stratum and destroys a geological theory.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it could have\"},{\"text\":\"been published to the world and its significance made known.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He had gone straight on working. As soon as he saw what the photograph\"},{\"text\":\"was, and what it meant, he had covered it up with another sheet of paper.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Luckily, when he unrolled it, it had been upside-down from the point of\"},{\"text\":\"view of the telescreen.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He took his scribbling pad on his knee and pushed back his chair so as\"}]","[{\"text\":\"keep your face\"},{\"text\":\"expressionless was not difficult, and even your breathing could be\"},{\"text\":\"controlled, with an effort: but you could not control the beating of your\"},{\"text\":\"heart, and the telescreen was quite delicate enough to pick it up. He let\"}]","[{\"text\":\"be ten minutes go by, tormented all the while by the\"},{\"text\":\"fear that some accident--a sudden draught blowing across his desk, for\"},{\"text\":\"instance--would betray him. Then, without uncovering it again, he dropped\"}]","[{\"text\":\"other waste papers.\"},{\"text\":\"Within another minute, perhaps, it would have crumbled into ashes.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"That was ten--eleven years ago. Today, probably, he would have kept that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it in his fingers\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to him to make a difference even now, when the photograph itself,\"},{\"text\":\"as well as the event it recorded, was only memory. Was the Party's hold\"},{\"text\":\"upon the past less strong, he wondered, because a piece of evidence which\"}]","[{\"text\":\"HAD ONCE existed?\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"But today, supposing that it could be somehow resurrected from its ashes,\"},{\"text\":\"the photograph might not even be evidence. Already, at the time when he\"},{\"text\":\"made his discovery, Oceania was no longer at war with Eurasia, and it must\"}]","[{\"text\":\"have been to the agents of Eastasia that the three dead men had betrayed\"},{\"text\":\"their country. Since then there had been other changes--two, three,\"},{\"text\":\"he could not remember how many. Very likely the confessions had been\"}]","[{\"text\":\"original facts and dates no longer\"},{\"text\":\"had the smallest significance. The past not only changed, but changed\"},{\"text\":\"continuously. What most afflicted him with the sense of nightmare was that\"},{\"text\":\"he had never clearly understood why the huge imposture was undertaken.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The immediate advantages of falsifying the past were obvious, but the\"},{\"text\":\"ultimate motive was mysterious. He took up his pen again and wrote:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"I do not understand WHY.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He wondered, as he had many times wondered before, whether he himself was\"},{\"text\":\"a lunatic. Perhaps a lunatic was simply a minority of one. At one time it\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that the earth goes round the sun;\"},{\"text\":\"today, to believe that the past is unalterable. He might be ALONE in\"},{\"text\":\"holding that belief, and if alone, then a lunatic. But the thought of being\"},{\"text\":\"a lunatic did not greatly trouble him: the horror was that he might also\"}]","[{\"text\":\"be wrong.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He picked up the children's history book and looked at the portrait of\"},{\"text\":\"Big Brother which formed its frontispiece. The hypnotic eyes gazed into\"},{\"text\":\"his own. It was as though some huge force were pressing down upon\"}]","[{\"text\":\"you--something that penetrated inside your skull, battering against your\"},{\"text\":\"brain, frightening you out of your beliefs, persuading you, almost, to\"},{\"text\":\"deny the evidence of your senses. In the end the Party would announce that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"have to believe it. It was inevitable\"},{\"text\":\"that they should make that claim sooner or later: the logic of their\"},{\"text\":\"position demanded it. Not merely the validity of experience, but the very\"},{\"text\":\"existence of external reality, was tacitly denied by their philosophy. The\"}]","[{\"text\":\"heresy of heresies was common sense. And what was terrifying was not that\"},{\"text\":\"they would kill you for thinking otherwise, but that they might be right.\"},{\"text\":\"For, after all, how do we know that two and two make four? Or that the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"past is unchangeable? If both the past\"},{\"text\":\"and the external world exist only in the mind, and if the mind itself is\"},{\"text\":\"controllable what then?\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"But no! His courage seemed suddenly to stiffen of its own accord. The face\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of O'Brien, not called up by any obvious association, had floated into his\"},{\"text\":\"mind. He knew, with more certainty than before, that O'Brien was on his\"},{\"text\":\"side. He was writing the diary for O'Brien--TO O'Brien: it was like an\"}]","[{\"text\":\"would ever read, but which was addressed\"},{\"text\":\"to a particular person and took its colour from that fact.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The Party told you to reject the evidence of your eyes and ears. It was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"His heart sank as he thought of\"},{\"text\":\"the enormous power arrayed against him, the ease with which any Party\"},{\"text\":\"intellectual would overthrow him in debate, the subtle arguments which he\"},{\"text\":\"would not be able to understand, much less answer. And yet he was in the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"right! They were wrong and he was right. The obvious, the silly, and the\"},{\"text\":\"true had got to be defended. Truisms are true, hold on to that! The solid\"},{\"text\":\"world exists, its laws do not change. Stones are hard, water is wet,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"earth's centre. With the feeling that\"},{\"text\":\"he was speaking to O'Brien, and also that he was setting forth an important\"},{\"text\":\"axiom, he wrote:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"two plus two make four. If that is\"},{\"text\":\"granted, all else follows.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Chapter 8\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"passage the smell of roasting\"},{\"text\":\"coffee--real coffee, not Victory Coffee--came floating out into the street.\"},{\"text\":\"Winston paused involuntarily. For perhaps two seconds he was back in the\"},{\"text\":\"half-forgotten world of his childhood. Then a door banged, seeming to cut\"}]","[{\"text\":\"off the smell as abruptly as though it had been a sound.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He had walked several kilometres over pavements, and his varicose ulcer\"},{\"text\":\"was throbbing. This was the second time in three weeks that he had missed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"rash act, since you could be certain\"},{\"text\":\"that the number of your attendances at the Centre was carefully checked.\"},{\"text\":\"In principle a Party member had no spare time, and was never alone except\"},{\"text\":\"in bed. It was assumed that when he was not working, eating, or sleeping\"}]","[{\"text\":\"he would be taking part in some kind of communal recreation: to do anything\"},{\"text\":\"that suggested a taste for solitude, even to go for a walk by yourself,\"},{\"text\":\"was always slightly dangerous. There was a word for it in Newspeak:\"}]","[{\"text\":\"individualism and eccentricity. But this\"},{\"text\":\"evening as he came out of the Ministry the balminess of the April air had\"},{\"text\":\"tempted him. The sky was a warmer blue than he had seen it that year, and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"boring, exhausting\"},{\"text\":\"games, the lectures, the creaking camaraderie oiled by gin, had seemed\"},{\"text\":\"intolerable. On impulse he had turned away from the bus-stop and wandered\"},{\"text\":\"off into the labyrinth of London, first south, then east, then north again,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"among unknown streets and hardly bothering in which\"},{\"text\":\"direction he was going.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'If there is hope,' he had written in the diary, 'it lies in the proles.'\"},{\"text\":\"The words kept coming back to him, statement of a mystical truth and a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"palpable absurdity. He was somewhere in the vague, brown-coloured slums\"},{\"text\":\"to the north and east of what had once been Saint Pancras Station. He was\"},{\"text\":\"walking up a cobbled street of little two-storey houses with battered\"}]","[{\"text\":\"pavement and which were somehow\"},{\"text\":\"curiously suggestive of ratholes. There were puddles of filthy water here\"},{\"text\":\"and there among the cobbles. In and out of the dark doorways, and down\"},{\"text\":\"narrow alley-ways that branched off on either side, people swarmed in\"}]","[{\"text\":\"astonishing numbers--girls in full bloom, with crudely lipsticked mouths,\"},{\"text\":\"and youths who chased the girls, and swollen waddling women who showed you\"},{\"text\":\"what the girls would be like in ten years' time, and old bent creatures\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ragged barefooted children who played\"},{\"text\":\"in the puddles and then scattered at angry yells from their mothers.\"},{\"text\":\"Perhaps a quarter of the windows in the street were broken and boarded up.\"},{\"text\":\"Most of the people paid no attention to Winston; a few eyed him with a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sort of guarded curiosity. Two monstrous women with brick-red forearms\"},{\"text\":\"folded across their aprons were talking outside a doorway. Winston caught\"},{\"text\":\"scraps of conversation as he approached.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"very well,\\\" I says. \\\"But if you'd of\"},{\"text\":\"been in my place you'd of done the same as what I done. It's easy to\"},{\"text\":\"criticize,\\\" I says, \\\"but you ain't got the same problems as what I got.\\\"'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it is.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The strident voices stopped abruptly. The women studied him in hostile\"},{\"text\":\"silence as he went past. But it was not hostility, exactly; merely a kind\"},{\"text\":\"of wariness, a momentary stiffening, as at the passing of some unfamiliar\"}]","[{\"text\":\"animal. The blue overalls of the Party could not be a common sight in a\"},{\"text\":\"street like this. Indeed, it was unwise to be seen in such places, unless\"},{\"text\":\"you had definite business there. The patrols might stop you if you happened\"}]","[{\"text\":\"papers, comrade? What are you doing here?\"},{\"text\":\"What time did you leave work? Is this your usual way home?'--and so on and\"},{\"text\":\"so forth. Not that there was any rule against walking home by an unusual\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Thought Police\"},{\"text\":\"heard about it.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Suddenly the whole street was in commotion. There were yells of warning\"},{\"text\":\"from all sides. People were shooting into the doorways like rabbits. A\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston, grabbed up a\"},{\"text\":\"tiny child playing in a puddle, whipped her apron round it, and leapt back\"},{\"text\":\"again, all in one movement. At the same instant a man in a concertina-like\"},{\"text\":\"black suit, who had emerged from a side alley, ran towards Winston,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"pointing excitedly to the sky.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Steamer!' he yelled. 'Look out, guv'nor! Bang over'ead! Lay down quick!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Steamer' was a nickname which, for some reason, the proles applied to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"himself on his face. The proles were\"},{\"text\":\"nearly always right when they gave you a warning of this kind. They seemed\"},{\"text\":\"to possess some kind of instinct which told them several seconds in advance\"},{\"text\":\"when a rocket was coming, although the rockets supposedly travelled faster\"}]","[{\"text\":\"than sound. Winston clasped his forearms above his head. There was a roar\"},{\"text\":\"that seemed to make the pavement heave; a shower of light objects pattered\"},{\"text\":\"on to his back. When he stood up he found that he was covered with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"window.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He walked on. The bomb had demolished a group of houses 200 metres up the\"},{\"text\":\"street. A black plume of smoke hung in the sky, and below it a cloud of\"},{\"text\":\"plaster dust in which a crowd was already forming around the ruins. There\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was a little pile of plaster lying on the pavement ahead of him, and in\"},{\"text\":\"the middle of it he could see a bright red streak. When he got up to it he\"},{\"text\":\"saw that it was a human hand severed at the wrist. Apart from the bloody\"}]","[{\"text\":\"whitened as to resemble a plaster cast.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He kicked the thing into the gutter, and then, to avoid the crowd, turned\"},{\"text\":\"down a side-street to the right. Within three or four minutes he was out\"}]","[{\"text\":\"affected, and the sordid swarming life of\"},{\"text\":\"the streets was going on as though nothing had happened. It was nearly\"},{\"text\":\"twenty hours, and the drinking-shops which the proles frequented ('pubs',\"}]","[{\"text\":\"grimy swing doors,\"},{\"text\":\"endlessly opening and shutting, there came forth a smell of urine, sawdust,\"},{\"text\":\"and sour beer. In an angle formed by a projecting house-front three men\"},{\"text\":\"were standing very close together, the middle one of them holding a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"newspaper which the other two were studying over his shoulder.\"},{\"text\":\"Even before he was near enough to make out the expression on their faces,\"},{\"text\":\"Winston could see absorption in every line of their bodies. It was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that they were reading. He was a few\"},{\"text\":\"paces away from them when suddenly the group broke up and two of the men\"},{\"text\":\"were in violent altercation. For a moment they seemed almost on the point\"},{\"text\":\"of blows.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"what I say? I tell you no number ending\"},{\"text\":\"in seven ain't won for over fourteen months!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes, it 'as, then!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'No, it 'as not! Back 'ome I got the 'ole lot of 'em for over two years\"}]","[{\"text\":\"wrote down on a piece of paper. I takes 'em down reg'lar as the clock. An'\"},{\"text\":\"I tell you, no number ending in seven----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes, a seven 'AS won! I could pretty near tell you the bleeding number.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in February--second week in February.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'February your grandmother! I got it all down in black and white. An' I\"},{\"text\":\"tell you, no number----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Oh, pack it in!' said the third man.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"They were talking about the Lottery. Winston looked back when he had gone\"},{\"text\":\"thirty metres. They were still arguing, with vivid, passionate faces.\"},{\"text\":\"The Lottery, with its weekly pay-out of enormous prizes, was the one public\"}]","[{\"text\":\"serious attention. It was probable that\"},{\"text\":\"there were some millions of proles for whom the Lottery was the principal\"},{\"text\":\"if not the only reason for remaining alive. It was their delight, their\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Where the Lottery was\"},{\"text\":\"concerned, even people who could barely read and write seemed capable of\"},{\"text\":\"intricate calculations and staggering feats of memory. There was a whole\"},{\"text\":\"tribe of men who made a living simply by selling systems, forecasts, and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"lucky amulets. Winston had nothing to do with the running of the Lottery,\"},{\"text\":\"which was managed by the Ministry of Plenty, but he was aware (indeed\"},{\"text\":\"everyone in the party was aware) that the prizes were largely imaginary.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"out, the winners of the big prizes being\"},{\"text\":\"non-existent persons. In the absence of any real intercommunication between\"},{\"text\":\"one part of Oceania and another, this was not difficult to arrange.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"proles. You had to cling on to that.\"},{\"text\":\"When you put it in words it sounded reasonable: it was when you looked at\"},{\"text\":\"the human beings passing you on the pavement that it became an act of\"},{\"text\":\"faith. The street into which he had turned ran downhill. He had a feeling\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that he had been in this neighbourhood before, and that there was a main\"},{\"text\":\"thoroughfare not far away. From somewhere ahead there came a din of\"},{\"text\":\"shouting voices. The street took a sharp turn and then ended in a flight\"}]","[{\"text\":\"alley where a few stall-keepers\"},{\"text\":\"were selling tired-looking vegetables. At this moment Winston remembered\"},{\"text\":\"where he was. The alley led out into the main street, and down the next\"},{\"text\":\"turning, not five minutes away, was the junk-shop where he had bought the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"blank book which was now his diary. And in a small stationer's shop not\"},{\"text\":\"far away he had bought his penholder and his bottle of ink.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He paused for a moment at the top of the steps. On the opposite side of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was a dingy little pub whose windows appeared to be frosted\"},{\"text\":\"over but in reality were merely coated with dust. A very old man, bent but\"},{\"text\":\"active, with white moustaches that bristled forward like those of a prawn,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in. As Winston stood watching, it\"},{\"text\":\"occurred to him that the old man, who must be eighty at the least, had\"},{\"text\":\"already been middle-aged when the Revolution happened. He and a few others\"},{\"text\":\"like him were the last links that now existed with the vanished world of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"capitalism. In the Party itself there were not many people left whose ideas\"},{\"text\":\"had been formed before the Revolution. The older generation had mostly\"},{\"text\":\"been wiped out in the great purges of the fifties and sixties, and the few\"}]","[{\"text\":\"terrified into complete intellectual\"},{\"text\":\"surrender. If there was any one still alive who could give you a truthful\"},{\"text\":\"account of conditions in the early part of the century, it could only be a\"},{\"text\":\"prole. Suddenly the passage from the history book that he had copied into\"}]","[{\"text\":\"his diary came back into Winston's mind, and a lunatic impulse took hold\"},{\"text\":\"of him. He would go into the pub, he would scrape acquaintance with that\"},{\"text\":\"old man and question him. He would say to him: 'Tell me about your life\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in those days? Were things better\"},{\"text\":\"than they are now, or were they worse?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Hurriedly, lest he should have time to become frightened, he descended the\"},{\"text\":\"steps and crossed the narrow street. It was madness of course. As usual,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"there was no definite rule against talking to proles and frequenting their\"},{\"text\":\"pubs, but it was far too unusual an action to pass unnoticed. If the\"},{\"text\":\"patrols appeared he might plead an attack of faintness, but it was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"He pushed open the door, and a hideous\"},{\"text\":\"cheesy smell of sour beer hit him in the face. As he entered the din of\"},{\"text\":\"voices dropped to about half its volume. Behind his back he could feel\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was going on at\"},{\"text\":\"the other end of the room interrupted itself for perhaps as much as thirty\"},{\"text\":\"seconds. The old man whom he had followed was standing at the bar, having\"},{\"text\":\"some kind of altercation with the barman, a large, stout, hook-nosed young\"}]","[{\"text\":\"forearms. A knot of others, standing round with glasses\"},{\"text\":\"in their hands, were watching the scene.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I arst you civil enough, didn't I?' said the old man, straightening his\"}]","[{\"text\":\"pint mug in the\"},{\"text\":\"'ole bleeding boozer?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'And what in hell's name IS a pint?' said the barman, leaning forward with\"},{\"text\":\"the tips of his fingers on the counter.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and don't know what a pint is! Why,\"},{\"text\":\"a pint's the 'alf of a quart, and there's four quarts to the gallon.\"},{\"text\":\"'Ave to teach you the A, B, C next.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Never heard of 'em,' said the barman shortly. 'Litre and half\"}]","[{\"text\":\"we serve. There's the glasses on the shelf in front\"},{\"text\":\"of you.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I likes a pint,' persisted the old man. 'You could 'a drawed me off a pint\"},{\"text\":\"easy enough. We didn't 'ave these bleeding litres when I was a young man.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'When you were a young man we were all living in the treetops,' said the\"},{\"text\":\"barman, with a glance at the other customers.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"There was a shout of laughter, and the uneasiness caused by Winston's entry\"}]","[{\"text\":\"white-stubbled face had flushed pink. He\"},{\"text\":\"turned away, muttering to himself, and bumped into Winston. Winston caught\"},{\"text\":\"him gently by the arm.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'May I offer you a drink?' he said.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"said the other, straightening his shoulders again. He\"},{\"text\":\"appeared not to have noticed Winston's blue overalls. 'Pint!' he added\"},{\"text\":\"aggressively to the barman. 'Pint of wallop.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"into thick glasses\"},{\"text\":\"which he had rinsed in a bucket under the counter. Beer was the only drink\"},{\"text\":\"you could get in prole pubs. The proles were supposed not to drink gin,\"},{\"text\":\"though in practice they could get hold of it easily enough. The game of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"swing again, and the knot of men at the bar had begun\"},{\"text\":\"talking about lottery tickets. Winston's presence was forgotten for a\"},{\"text\":\"moment. There was a deal table under the window where he and the old man\"}]","[{\"text\":\"horribly dangerous, but\"},{\"text\":\"at any rate there was no telescreen in the room, a point he had made sure\"},{\"text\":\"of as soon as he came in.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"''E could 'a drawed me off a pint,' grumbled the old man as he settled down\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'alf litre ain't enough. It don't satisfy. And a 'ole\"},{\"text\":\"litre's too much. It starts my bladder running. Let alone the price.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'You must have seen great changes since you were a young man,' said\"},{\"text\":\"Winston tentatively.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The old man's pale blue eyes moved from the darts board to the bar, and\"},{\"text\":\"from the bar to the door of the Gents, as though it were in the bar-room\"},{\"text\":\"that he expected the changes to have occurred.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"finally. 'And cheaper! When I was a young\"},{\"text\":\"man, mild beer--wallop we used to call it--was fourpence a pint. That was\"},{\"text\":\"before the war, of course.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Which war was that?' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"said the old man vaguely. He took up his glass, and his\"},{\"text\":\"shoulders straightened again. ''Ere's wishing you the very best of 'ealth!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"In his lean throat the sharp-pointed Adam's apple made a surprisingly rapid\"}]","[{\"text\":\"vanished. Winston went to the bar and\"},{\"text\":\"came back with two more half-litres. The old man appeared to have forgotten\"},{\"text\":\"his prejudice against drinking a full litre.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'You are very much older than I am,' said Winston. 'You must have been a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"grown man before I was born. You can remember what it was like in the old\"},{\"text\":\"days, before the Revolution. People of my age don't really know anything\"},{\"text\":\"about those times. We can only read about them in books, and what it says\"}]","[{\"text\":\"should like your opinion on that. The\"},{\"text\":\"history books say that life before the Revolution was completely different\"},{\"text\":\"from what it is now. There was the most terrible oppression, injustice,\"},{\"text\":\"poverty worse than anything we can imagine. Here in London, the great mass\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of the people never had enough to eat from birth to death. Half of them\"},{\"text\":\"hadn't even boots on their feet. They worked twelve hours a day, they left\"},{\"text\":\"school at nine, they slept ten in a room. And at the same time there were\"}]","[{\"text\":\"thousands--the capitalists, they were\"},{\"text\":\"called--who were rich and powerful. They owned everything that there was\"},{\"text\":\"to own. They lived in great gorgeous houses with thirty servants, they\"},{\"text\":\"rode about in motor-cars and four-horse carriages, they drank champagne,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"they wore top hats----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The old man brightened suddenly.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Top 'ats!' he said. 'Funny you should mention 'em. The same thing come\"},{\"text\":\"into my 'ead only yesterday, I dono why. I was jest thinking, I ain't seen\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a top 'at in years. Gorn right out, they 'ave. The last time I wore one\"},{\"text\":\"was at my sister-in-law's funeral. And that was--well, I couldn't give you\"},{\"text\":\"the date, but it must'a been fifty years ago. Of course it was only 'ired\"},{\"text\":\"for the occasion, you understand.'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'It isn't very important about the top hats,' said Winston patiently.\"},{\"text\":\"'The point is, these capitalists--they and a few lawyers and priests and\"},{\"text\":\"so forth who lived on them--were the lords of the earth. Everything existed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"people, the workers--were their\"},{\"text\":\"slaves. They could do what they liked with you. They could ship you off to\"},{\"text\":\"Canada like cattle. They could sleep with your daughters if they chose.\"},{\"text\":\"They could order you to be flogged with something called a cat-o'-nine\"}]","[{\"text\":\"tails. You had to take your cap off when you passed them. Every capitalist\"},{\"text\":\"went about with a gang of lackeys who----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The old man brightened again.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"since ever so long.\"},{\"text\":\"Lackeys! That reg'lar takes me back, that does. I recollect--oh, donkey's\"},{\"text\":\"years ago--I used to sometimes go to 'Yde Park of a Sunday afternoon to\"},{\"text\":\"'ear the blokes making speeches. Salvation Army, Roman Catholics, Jews,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Indians--all sorts there was. And there was one bloke--well, I couldn't\"},{\"text\":\"give you 'is name, but a real powerful speaker 'e was. 'E didn't 'alf\"},{\"text\":\"give it 'em! \\\"Lackeys!\\\" 'e says, \\\"lackeys of the bourgeoisie! Flunkies of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was another of them. And 'yenas--'e\"},{\"text\":\"definitely called 'em 'yenas. Of course 'e was referring to the Labour\"},{\"text\":\"Party, you understand.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston had the feeling that they were talking at cross-purposes.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'What I really wanted to know was this,' he said. 'Do you feel that you\"},{\"text\":\"have more freedom now than you had in those days? Are you treated more\"},{\"text\":\"like a human being? In the old days, the rich people, the people at the\"},{\"text\":\"top----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'The 'Ouse of Lords,' put in the old man reminiscently.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'The House of Lords, if you like. What I am asking is, were these people\"},{\"text\":\"able to treat you as an inferior, simply because they were rich and you\"}]","[{\"text\":\"instance, that you had to call them \\\"Sir\\\" and\"},{\"text\":\"take off your cap when you passed them?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The old man appeared to think deeply. He drank off about a quarter of his\"},{\"text\":\"beer before answering.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Yes,' he said. 'They liked you to touch your cap to 'em. It showed\"},{\"text\":\"respect, like. I didn't agree with it, myself, but I done it often enough.\"},{\"text\":\"Had to, as you might say.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"history books--was\"},{\"text\":\"it usual for these people and their servants to push you off the pavement\"},{\"text\":\"into the gutter?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'One of 'em pushed me once,' said the old man. 'I recollect it as if it\"}]","[{\"text\":\"they used to get on\"},{\"text\":\"Boat Race night--and I bumps into a young bloke on Shaftesbury Avenue.\"},{\"text\":\"Quite a gent, 'e was--dress shirt, top 'at, black overcoat. 'E was kind\"},{\"text\":\"of zig-zagging across the pavement, and I bumps into 'im accidental-like.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'E says, \\\"Why can't you look where you're going?\\\" 'e says. I say, \\\"Ju think\"},{\"text\":\"you've bought the bleeding pavement?\\\" 'E says, \\\"I'll twist your bloody 'ead\"},{\"text\":\"off if you get fresh with me.\\\" I says, \\\"You're drunk. I'll give you in\"}]","[{\"text\":\"if you'll believe me, 'e puts 'is\"},{\"text\":\"'and on my chest and gives me a shove as pretty near sent me under the\"},{\"text\":\"wheels of a bus. Well, I was young in them days, and I was going to 'ave\"},{\"text\":\"fetched 'im one, only----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"helplessness took hold of Winston. The old man's memory was\"},{\"text\":\"nothing but a rubbish-heap of details. One could question him all day\"},{\"text\":\"without getting any real information. The party histories might still be\"}]","[{\"text\":\"even be completely true. He made a last\"},{\"text\":\"attempt.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Perhaps I have not made myself clear,' he said. 'What I'm trying to say\"},{\"text\":\"is this. You have been alive a very long time; you lived half your life\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Revolution. In 1925, for instance, you were already grown up.\"},{\"text\":\"Would you say from what you can remember, that life in 1925 was better\"},{\"text\":\"than it is now, or worse? If you could choose, would you prefer to live\"},{\"text\":\"then or now?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The old man looked meditatively at the darts board. He finished up his\"},{\"text\":\"beer, more slowly than before. When he spoke it was with a tolerant\"},{\"text\":\"philosophical air, as though the beer had mellowed him.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"he said. 'You expect me to say as I'd\"},{\"text\":\"sooner be young again. Most people'd say they'd sooner be young, if you\"},{\"text\":\"arst 'em. You got your 'ealth and strength when you're young. When you\"},{\"text\":\"get to my time of life you ain't never well. I suffer something wicked\"}]","[{\"text\":\"from my feet, and my bladder's jest terrible. Six and seven times a night\"},{\"text\":\"it 'as me out of bed. On the other 'and, there's great advantages in being\"},{\"text\":\"a old man. You ain't got the same worries. No truck with women, and that's\"}]","[{\"text\":\"for near on thirty year, if you'd\"},{\"text\":\"credit it. Nor wanted to, what's more.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston sat back against the window-sill. It was no use going on. He was\"},{\"text\":\"about to buy some more beer when the old man suddenly got up and shuffled\"}]","[{\"text\":\"rapidly into the stinking urinal at the side of the room. The extra\"},{\"text\":\"half-litre was already working on him. Winston sat for a minute or two\"},{\"text\":\"gazing at his empty glass, and hardly noticed when his feet carried him out\"}]","[{\"text\":\"years at the most, he reflected, the\"},{\"text\":\"huge and simple question, 'Was life better before the Revolution than it\"},{\"text\":\"is now?' would have ceased once and for all to be answerable. But in effect\"},{\"text\":\"it was unanswerable even now, since the few scattered survivors from the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ancient world were incapable of comparing one age with another. They\"},{\"text\":\"remembered a million useless things, a quarrel with a workmate, a hunt for\"},{\"text\":\"a lost bicycle pump, the expression on a long-dead sister's face, the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"seventy years ago: but all the relevant\"},{\"text\":\"facts were outside the range of their vision. They were like the ant,\"},{\"text\":\"which can see small objects but not large ones. And when memory failed and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"claim of the Party\"},{\"text\":\"to have improved the conditions of human life had got to be accepted,\"},{\"text\":\"because there did not exist, and never again could exist, any standard\"},{\"text\":\"against which it could be tested.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"stopped abruptly. He halted and looked\"},{\"text\":\"up. He was in a narrow street, with a few dark little shops, interspersed\"},{\"text\":\"among dwelling-houses. Immediately above his head there hung three\"}]","[{\"text\":\"been gilded. He\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to know the place. Of course! He was standing outside the junk-shop\"},{\"text\":\"where he had bought the diary.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"A twinge of fear went through him. It had been a sufficiently rash act to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"had sworn never to come near the\"},{\"text\":\"place again. And yet the instant that he allowed his thoughts to wander,\"},{\"text\":\"his feet had brought him back here of their own accord. It was precisely\"},{\"text\":\"against suicidal impulses of this kind that he had hoped to guard himself\"}]","[{\"text\":\"by opening the diary. At the same time he noticed that although it was\"},{\"text\":\"nearly twenty-one hours the shop was still open. With the feeling that he\"},{\"text\":\"would be less conspicuous inside than hanging about on the pavement, he\"}]","[{\"text\":\"questioned, he could plausibly say that\"},{\"text\":\"he was trying to buy razor blades.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The proprietor had just lighted a hanging oil lamp which gave off an\"},{\"text\":\"unclean but friendly smell. He was a man of perhaps sixty, frail and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"bowed, with a long, benevolent nose, and mild eyes distorted by thick\"},{\"text\":\"spectacles. His hair was almost white, but his eyebrows were bushy and\"},{\"text\":\"still black. His spectacles, his gentle, fussy movements, and the fact\"}]","[{\"text\":\"black velvet, gave him a vague air\"},{\"text\":\"of intellectuality, as though he had been some kind of literary man, or\"},{\"text\":\"perhaps a musician. His voice was soft, as though faded, and his accent\"},{\"text\":\"less debased than that of the majority of proles.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'I recognized you on the pavement,' he said immediately. 'You're the\"},{\"text\":\"gentleman that bought the young lady's keepsake album. That was a beautiful\"},{\"text\":\"bit of paper, that was. Cream-laid, it used to be called. There's been no\"}]","[{\"text\":\"say fifty years.' He peered at Winston\"},{\"text\":\"over the top of his spectacles. 'Is there anything special I can do for\"},{\"text\":\"you? Or did you just want to look round?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in. I don't want\"},{\"text\":\"anything in particular.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It's just as well,' said the other, 'because I don't suppose I could have\"},{\"text\":\"satisfied you.' He made an apologetic gesture with his softpalmed hand.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"you might say. Between you and me, the\"},{\"text\":\"antique trade's just about finished. No demand any longer, and no stock\"},{\"text\":\"either. Furniture, china, glass it's all been broken up by degrees. And\"}]","[{\"text\":\"haven't seen a brass\"},{\"text\":\"candlestick in years.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The tiny interior of the shop was in fact uncomfortably full, but there\"},{\"text\":\"was almost nothing in it of the slightest value. The floorspace was very\"}]","[{\"text\":\"because all round the walls were stacked innumerable dusty\"},{\"text\":\"picture-frames. In the window there were trays of nuts and bolts, worn-out\"},{\"text\":\"chisels, penknives with broken blades, tarnished watches that did not even\"}]","[{\"text\":\"other miscellaneous rubbish. Only on a\"},{\"text\":\"small table in the corner was there a litter of odds and ends--lacquered\"},{\"text\":\"snuffboxes, agate brooches, and the like--which looked as though they might\"}]","[{\"text\":\"towards the table his\"},{\"text\":\"eye was caught by a round, smooth thing that gleamed softly in the\"},{\"text\":\"lamplight, and he picked it up.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"It was a heavy lump of glass, curved on one side, flat on the other, making\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hemisphere. There was a peculiar softness, as of rainwater, in\"},{\"text\":\"both the colour and the texture of the glass. At the heart of it, magnified\"},{\"text\":\"by the curved surface, there was a strange, pink, convoluted object that\"},{\"text\":\"recalled a rose or a sea anemone.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'What is it?' said Winston, fascinated.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'That's coral, that is,' said the old man. 'It must have come from the\"},{\"text\":\"Indian Ocean. They used to kind of embed it in the glass. That wasn't made\"}]","[{\"text\":\"by the look of it.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It's a beautiful thing,' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It is a beautiful thing,' said the other appreciatively. 'But there's not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"happened that you\"},{\"text\":\"wanted to buy it, that'd cost you four dollars. I can remember when a thing\"},{\"text\":\"like that would have fetched eight pounds, and eight pounds was--well, I\"},{\"text\":\"can't work it out, but it was a lot of money. But who cares about genuine\"}]","[{\"text\":\"nowadays--even the few that's left?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston immediately paid over the four dollars and slid the coveted thing\"},{\"text\":\"into his pocket. What appealed to him about it was not so much its beauty\"}]","[{\"text\":\"quite different\"},{\"text\":\"from the present one. The soft, rainwatery glass was not like any glass\"},{\"text\":\"that he had ever seen. The thing was doubly attractive because of its\"},{\"text\":\"apparent uselessness, though he could guess that it must once have been\"}]","[{\"text\":\"paperweight. It was very heavy in his pocket, but fortunately\"},{\"text\":\"it did not make much of a bulge. It was a queer thing, even a compromising\"},{\"text\":\"thing, for a Party member to have in his possession. Anything old, and for\"}]","[{\"text\":\"always vaguely suspect. The old man had\"},{\"text\":\"grown noticeably more cheerful after receiving the four dollars. Winston\"},{\"text\":\"realized that he would have accepted three or even two.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"take a look at,' he\"},{\"text\":\"said. 'There's not much in it. Just a few pieces. We'll do with a light if\"},{\"text\":\"we're going upstairs.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He lit another lamp, and, with bowed back, led the way slowly up the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"stairs and along a tiny passage, into a room which did\"},{\"text\":\"not give on the street but looked out on a cobbled yard and a forest of\"},{\"text\":\"chimney-pots. Winston noticed that the furniture was still arranged as\"}]","[{\"text\":\"strip of carpet on\"},{\"text\":\"the floor, a picture or two on the walls, and a deep, slatternly arm-chair\"},{\"text\":\"drawn up to the fireplace. An old-fashioned glass clock with a twelve-hour\"},{\"text\":\"face was ticking away on the mantelpiece. Under the window, and occupying\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of the room, was an enormous bed with the mattress still\"},{\"text\":\"on it.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'We lived here till my wife died,' said the old man half apologetically.\"},{\"text\":\"'I'm selling the furniture off by little and little. Now that's a beautiful\"}]","[{\"text\":\"at least it would be if you could get the bugs out of it.\"},{\"text\":\"But I dare say you'd find it a little bit cumbersome.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He was holding the lamp high up, so as to illuminate the whole room, and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"looked curiously inviting. The thought\"},{\"text\":\"flitted through Winston's mind that it would probably be quite easy to\"},{\"text\":\"rent the room for a few dollars a week, if he dared to take the risk. It\"}]","[{\"text\":\"as thought of; but\"},{\"text\":\"the room had awakened in him a sort of nostalgia, a sort of ancestral\"},{\"text\":\"memory. It seemed to him that he knew exactly what it felt like to sit in\"},{\"text\":\"a room like this, in an arm-chair beside an open fire with your feet in\"}]","[{\"text\":\"kettle on the hob; utterly alone, utterly secure, with\"},{\"text\":\"nobody watching you, no voice pursuing you, no sound except the singing\"},{\"text\":\"of the kettle and the friendly ticking of the clock.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'There's no telescreen!' he could not help murmuring.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Ah,' said the old man, 'I never had one of those things. Too expensive.\"},{\"text\":\"And I never seemed to feel the need of it, somehow. Now that's a nice\"},{\"text\":\"gateleg table in the corner there. Though of course you'd have to put new\"}]","[{\"text\":\"flaps.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"There was a small bookcase in the other corner, and Winston had already\"},{\"text\":\"gravitated towards it. It contained nothing but rubbish. The hunting-down\"},{\"text\":\"and destruction of books had been done with the same thoroughness in the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"prole quarters as everywhere else. It was very unlikely that there existed\"},{\"text\":\"anywhere in Oceania a copy of a book printed earlier than 1960. The old\"},{\"text\":\"man, still carrying the lamp, was standing in front of 