al ones, that is.'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston wondered vaguely to what century the church belonged. It was always\"},{\"text\":\"difficult to determine the age of a London building. Anything large and\"},{\"text\":\"impressive, if it was reasonably new in appearance, was automatically\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the Revolution, while anything that was\"},{\"text\":\"obviously of earlier date was ascribed to some dim period called the Middle\"},{\"text\":\"Ages. The centuries of capitalism were held to have produced nothing of any\"}]","[{\"text\":\"more than one\"},{\"text\":\"could learn it from books. Statues, inscriptions, memorial stones, the\"},{\"text\":\"names of streets--anything that might throw light upon the past had been\"},{\"text\":\"systematically altered.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"he said.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'There's a lot of them left, really,' said the old man, 'though they've\"},{\"text\":\"been put to other uses. Now, how did that rhyme go? Ah! I've got it!\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"\\\"Oranges and lemons, say the bells of St Clement's,\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"ou owe me three farthings, say the bells of St Martin's----\\\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"get. A farthing, that was a small copper\"},{\"text\":\"coin, looked something like a cent.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Where was St Martin's?' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'St Martin's? That's still standing. It's in Victory Square, alongside the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"picture gallery. A building with a kind of a triangular porch and pillars\"},{\"text\":\"in front, and a big flight of steps.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston knew the place well. It was a museum used for propaganda displays\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Floating Fortresses,\"},{\"text\":\"waxwork tableaux illustrating enemy atrocities, and the like.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'St Martin's