text\":\"a friendly smile. The silly blond face beamed into his. Winston had a\"},{\"text\":\"hallucination of himself smashing a pick-axe right into the middle of it.\"},{\"text\":\"The girl's table filled up a few minutes later.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"But she must have seen him coming towards her, and perhaps she would take\"},{\"text\":\"the hint. Next day he took care to arrive early. Surely enough, she was at\"},{\"text\":\"a table in about the same place, and again alone. The person immediately\"}]","[{\"text\":\"small, swiftly-moving, beetle-like man\"},{\"text\":\"with a flat face and tiny, suspicious eyes. As Winston turned away from\"},{\"text\":\"the counter with his tray, he saw that the little man was making straight\"}]","[{\"text\":\"vacant place at a\"},{\"text\":\"table further away, but something in the little man's appearance suggested\"},{\"text\":\"that he would be sufficiently attentive to his own comfort to choose the\"},{\"text\":\"emptiest table. With ice at his heart Winston followed. It was no use\"}]","[{\"text\":\"get the girl alone. At this moment there was a tremendous\"},{\"text\":\"crash. The little man was sprawling on all fours, his tray had gone flying,\"},{\"text\":\"two streams of soup and coffee were flowing across the floor. He started\"}]","[{\"text\":\"at Winston, whom he evidently\"},{\"text\":\"suspected of having tripped him up. But it was all right. Five seconds\"},{\"text\":\"later, with a thundering heart, Winston was sitting at the girl's table.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"promptly began eating.\"},{\"text\":\"It was all-important to speak at once, before anyone else came, but now\"},{\"text\":\"a terrible fear had taken possession of him. A week had gone by since\"},{\"text\":\"she had first approached him. She would have changed her mind, she must\"}]","[{\"text\":\"have changed her mind! It was impossible that this affair should end\"},{\"text\":\"successfully; such things did not happen in real life. He might have\"},{\"text\":\"flinched altogether from speaking if at this moment he had not seen\"}]","[{\"text\":\"wandering limply round the room with\"},{\"text\":\"a tray, looking for a place to sit down. In his vague way Ampleforth\"},{\"text\":\"was attached to Winston, and would certainly sit down at his table if\"},{\"text\":\"he caught sight of him. There was perhaps a minute in which to act. Both\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston and the girl were eating steadily. The stuff they were eating was\"},{\"text\":\"a thin stew, actually a soup, of haricot beans. In a low murmur Winston\"},{\"text\":\"began speaking. Neither of them looked up; steadily they spooned the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"between spoonfuls exchanged the few\"},{\"text\":\"necessary words in low expressionless voices.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What time do you leave work?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Eighteen-thirty.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Where can we meet?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Victory Square, near the monument.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It's full of telescreens.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It doesn't matter if there's a crowd.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Any signal?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"see me among a lot of people. And don't\"},{\"text\":\"look at me. Just keep somewhere near me.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What time?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Nineteen hours.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'All right.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to see Winston and sat down at another table. They did\"},{\"text\":\"not speak again, and, so far as it was possible for two people sitting on\"},{\"text\":\"opposite sides of the same table, they did not look at one another. The\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston stayed to\"},{\"text\":\"smoke a cigarette.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston was in Victory Square before the appointed time. He wandered round\"},{\"text\":\"the base of the enormous fluted column, at the top of which Big Brother's\"}]","[{\"text\":\"vanquished the\"},{\"text\":\"Eurasian aeroplanes (the Eastasian aeroplanes, it had been, a few years\"},{\"text\":\"ago) in the Battle of Airstrip One. In the street in front of it there was\"},{\"text\":\"a statue of a man on horseback which was supposed to represent Oliver\"}]","[{\"text\":\"minutes past the hour the girl had still not appeared.\"},{\"text\":\"Again the terrible fear seized upon Winston. She was not coming, she had\"},{\"text\":\"changed her mind! He walked slowly up to the north side of the square and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Martin's Church,\"},{\"text\":\"whose bells, when it had bells, had chimed 'You owe me three farthings.'\"},{\"text\":\"Then he saw the girl standing at the base of the monument, reading or\"},{\"text\":\"pretending to read a poster which ran spirally up the column. It was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"her until some more people had accumulated. There were\"},{\"text\":\"telescreens all round the pediment. But at this moment there was a din of\"},{\"text\":\"shouting and a zoom of heavy vehicles from somewhere to the left. Suddenly\"}]","[{\"text\":\"girl nipped nimbly\"},{\"text\":\"round the lions at the base of the monument and joined in the rush.\"},{\"text\":\"Winston followed. As he ran, he gathered from some shouted remarks that\"},{\"text\":\"a convoy of Eurasian prisoners was passing.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"mass of people was blocking the south side of the square.\"},{\"text\":\"Winston, at normal times the kind of person who gravitates to the outer\"},{\"text\":\"edge of any kind of scrimmage, shoved, butted, squirmed his way forward\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was within arm's length of the girl,\"},{\"text\":\"but the way was blocked by an enormous prole and an almost equally enormous\"},{\"text\":\"woman, presumably his wife, who seemed to form an impenetrable wall of\"},{\"text\":\"flesh. Winston wriggled himself sideways, and with a violent lunge managed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to drive his shoulder between them. For a moment it felt as though his\"},{\"text\":\"entrails were being ground to pulp between the two muscular hips, then he\"},{\"text\":\"had broken through, sweating a little. He was next to the girl. They were\"}]","[{\"text\":\"fixedly in front of them.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"A long line of trucks, with wooden-faced guards armed with sub-machine\"},{\"text\":\"guns standing upright in each corner, was passing slowly down the street.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"uniforms were squatting,\"},{\"text\":\"jammed close together. Their sad, Mongolian faces gazed out over the sides\"},{\"text\":\"of the trucks utterly incurious. Occasionally when a truck jolted there\"},{\"text\":\"was a clank-clank of metal: all the prisoners were wearing leg-irons.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Truck-load after truck-load of the sad faces passed. Winston knew they\"},{\"text\":\"were there but he saw them only intermittently. The girl's shoulder, and\"},{\"text\":\"her arm right down to the elbow, were pressed against his. Her cheek was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"its warmth. She had immediately taken\"},{\"text\":\"charge of the situation, just as she had done in the canteen. She began\"},{\"text\":\"speaking in the same expressionless voice as before, with lips barely\"},{\"text\":\"moving, a mere murmur easily drowned by the din of voices and the rumbling\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of the trucks.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Can you hear me?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Can you get Sunday afternoon off?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to Paddington\"},{\"text\":\"Station----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"With a sort of military precision that astonished him, she outlined the\"},{\"text\":\"route that he was to follow. A half-hour railway journey; turn left outside\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the top bar\"},{\"text\":\"missing; a path across a field; a grass-grown lane; a track between bushes;\"},{\"text\":\"a dead tree with moss on it. It was as though she had a map inside her\"},{\"text\":\"head. 'Can you remember all that?' she murmured finally.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes.'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'You turn left, then right, then left again. And the gate's got no top bar.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes. What time?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'About fifteen. You may have to wait. I'll get there by another way. Are\"},{\"text\":\"you sure you remember everything?'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Yes.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Then get away from me as quick as you can.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"She need not have told him that. But for the moment they could not\"},{\"text\":\"extricate themselves from the crowd. The trucks were still filing past,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the people still insatiably gaping. At the start there had been a few boos\"},{\"text\":\"and hisses, but it came only from the Party members among the crowd, and\"},{\"text\":\"had soon stopped. The prevailing emotion was simply curiosity. Foreigners,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Eastasia, were a kind of strange animal. One\"},{\"text\":\"literally never saw them except in the guise of prisoners, and even as\"},{\"text\":\"prisoners one never got more than a momentary glimpse of them. Nor did\"}]","[{\"text\":\"were hanged as\"},{\"text\":\"war-criminals: the others simply vanished, presumably into forced-labour\"},{\"text\":\"camps. The round Mogol faces had given way to faces of a more European\"},{\"text\":\"type, dirty, bearded and exhausted. From over scrubby cheekbones eyes\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston's, sometimes with strange intensity, and flashed away\"},{\"text\":\"again. The convoy was drawing to an end. In the last truck he could see an\"},{\"text\":\"aged man, his face a mass of grizzled hair, standing upright with wrists\"}]","[{\"text\":\"were used to having them bound\"},{\"text\":\"together. It was almost time for Winston and the girl to part. But at the\"},{\"text\":\"last moment, while the crowd still hemmed them in, her hand felt for his\"},{\"text\":\"and gave it a fleeting squeeze.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"been ten seconds, and yet it seemed a long time that\"},{\"text\":\"their hands were clasped together. He had time to learn every detail\"},{\"text\":\"of her hand. He explored the long fingers, the shapely nails, the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"flesh under the\"},{\"text\":\"wrist. Merely from feeling it he would have known it by sight. In the\"},{\"text\":\"same instant it occurred to him that he did not know what colour the\"},{\"text\":\"girl's eyes were. They were probably brown, but people with dark hair\"}]","[{\"text\":\"eyes. To turn his head and look at her would have\"},{\"text\":\"been inconceivable folly. With hands locked together, invisible among\"},{\"text\":\"the press of bodies, they stared steadily in front of them, and instead\"}]","[{\"text\":\"gazed mournfully\"},{\"text\":\"at Winston out of nests of hair.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Chapter 2\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and shade,\"},{\"text\":\"stepping out into pools of gold wherever the boughs parted. Under the\"},{\"text\":\"trees to the left of him the ground was misty with bluebells. The air\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to kiss one's skin. It was the second of May. From somewhere deeper\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the wood came the droning of ring-doves.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He was a bit early. There had been no difficulties about the journey, and\"},{\"text\":\"the girl was so evidently experienced that he was less frightened than he\"}]","[{\"text\":\"she could be trusted to find a safe\"},{\"text\":\"place. In general you could not assume that you were much safer in the\"},{\"text\":\"country than in London. There were no telescreens, of course, but there\"},{\"text\":\"was always the danger of concealed microphones by which your voice might\"}]","[{\"text\":\"be picked up and recognized; besides, it was not easy to make a journey\"},{\"text\":\"by yourself without attracting attention. For distances of less than\"},{\"text\":\"100 kilometres it was not necessary to get your passport endorsed, but\"}]","[{\"text\":\"about the railway stations, who\"},{\"text\":\"examined the papers of any Party member they found there and asked awkward\"},{\"text\":\"questions. However, no patrols had appeared, and on the walk from the\"},{\"text\":\"station he had made sure by cautious backward glances that he was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"being followed. The train was full of proles, in holiday mood because of\"},{\"text\":\"the summery weather. The wooden-seated carriage in which he travelled was\"},{\"text\":\"filled to overflowing by a single enormous family, ranging from a toothless\"}]","[{\"text\":\"baby, going out to spend an afternoon\"},{\"text\":\"with 'in-laws' in the country, and, as they freely explained to Winston,\"},{\"text\":\"to get hold of a little black-market butter.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The lane widened, and in a minute he came to the footpath she had told him\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of, a mere cattle-track which plunged between the bushes. He had no watch,\"},{\"text\":\"but it could not be fifteen yet. The bluebells were so thick underfoot\"},{\"text\":\"that it was impossible not to tread on them. He knelt down and began\"}]","[{\"text\":\"away, but also from a vague idea that\"},{\"text\":\"he would like to have a bunch of flowers to offer to the girl when they\"},{\"text\":\"met. He had got together a big bunch and was smelling their faint sickly\"},{\"text\":\"scent when a sound at his back froze him, the unmistakable crackle of a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"foot on twigs. He went on picking bluebells. It was the best thing to do.\"},{\"text\":\"It might be the girl, or he might have been followed after all. To look\"},{\"text\":\"round was to show guilt. He picked another and another. A hand fell\"},{\"text\":\"lightly on his shoulder.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"He looked up. It was the girl. She shook her head, evidently as a warning\"},{\"text\":\"that he must keep silent, then parted the bushes and quickly led the way\"},{\"text\":\"along the narrow track into the wood. Obviously she had been that way\"}]","[{\"text\":\"as though by habit. Winston followed,\"},{\"text\":\"still clasping his bunch of flowers. His first feeling was relief, but as\"},{\"text\":\"he watched the strong slender body moving in front of him, with the scarlet\"},{\"text\":\"sash that was just tight enough to bring out the curve of her hips, the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sense of his own inferiority was heavy upon him. Even now it seemed quite\"},{\"text\":\"likely that when she turned round and looked at him she would draw back\"},{\"text\":\"after all. The sweetness of the air and the greenness of the leaves daunted\"}]","[{\"text\":\"station the May sunshine had made him\"},{\"text\":\"feel dirty and etiolated, a creature of indoors, with the sooty dust of\"},{\"text\":\"London in the pores of his skin. It occurred to him that till now she had\"},{\"text\":\"probably never seen him in broad daylight in the open. They came to the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"fallen tree that she had spoken of. The girl hopped over and forced apart\"},{\"text\":\"the bushes, in which there did not seem to be an opening. When Winston\"},{\"text\":\"followed her, he found that they were in a natural clearing, a tiny grassy\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that shut it in completely. The girl\"},{\"text\":\"stopped and turned.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Here we are,' she said.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He was facing her at several paces' distance. As yet he did not dare move\"},{\"text\":\"nearer to her.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'I didn't want to say anything in the lane,' she went on, 'in case there's\"},{\"text\":\"a mike hidden there. I don't suppose there is, but there could be. There's\"},{\"text\":\"always the chance of one of those swine recognizing your voice. We're all\"},{\"text\":\"right here.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"He still had not the courage to approach her. 'We're all right here?'\"},{\"text\":\"he repeated stupidly.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes. Look at the trees.' They were small ashes, which at some time had\"}]","[{\"text\":\"poles, none of\"},{\"text\":\"them thicker than one's wrist. 'There's nothing big enough to hide a mike\"},{\"text\":\"in. Besides, I've been here before.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"They were only making conversation. He had managed to move closer to her\"}]","[{\"text\":\"upright, with a smile on her face that\"},{\"text\":\"looked faintly ironical, as though she were wondering why he was so slow\"},{\"text\":\"to act. The bluebells had cascaded on to the ground. They seemed to have\"},{\"text\":\"fallen of their own accord. He took her hand.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Would you believe,' he said, 'that till this moment I didn't know what\"},{\"text\":\"colour your eyes were?' They were brown, he noted, a rather light shade of\"},{\"text\":\"brown, with dark lashes. 'Now that you've seen what I'm really like,\"},{\"text\":\"can you still bear to look at me?'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Yes, easily.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I'm thirty-nine years old. I've got a wife that I can't get rid of. I've\"},{\"text\":\"got varicose veins. I've got five false teeth.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I couldn't care less,' said the girl.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The next moment, it was hard to say by whose act, she was in his arms.\"},{\"text\":\"At the beginning he had no feeling except sheer incredulity. The youthful\"},{\"text\":\"body was strained against his own, the mass of dark hair was against his\"}]","[{\"text\":\"turned her face up and he was kissing the\"},{\"text\":\"wide red mouth. She had clasped her arms about his neck, she was calling\"},{\"text\":\"him darling, precious one, loved one. He had pulled her down on to the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"liked with her.\"},{\"text\":\"But the truth was that he had no physical sensation, except that of mere\"},{\"text\":\"contact. All he felt was incredulity and pride. He was glad that this was\"},{\"text\":\"happening, but he had no physical desire. It was too soon, her youth and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"frightened him, he was too much used to living without\"},{\"text\":\"women--he did not know the reason. The girl picked herself up and pulled a\"},{\"text\":\"bluebell out of her hair. She sat against him, putting her arm round his\"},{\"text\":\"waist.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"There's no hurry. We've got the whole afternoon. Isn't\"},{\"text\":\"this a splendid hide-out? I found it when I got lost once on a community\"},{\"text\":\"hike. If anyone was coming you could hear them a hundred metres away.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What is your name?' said Winston.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Julia. I know yours. It's Winston--Winston Smith.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'How did you find that out?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I expect I'm better at finding things out than you are, dear. Tell me,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"note?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He did not feel any temptation to tell lies to her. It was even a sort of\"},{\"text\":\"love-offering to start off by telling the worst.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I hated the sight of you,' he said. 'I wanted to rape you and then murder\"}]","[{\"text\":\"you afterwards. Two weeks ago I thought seriously of smashing your head in\"},{\"text\":\"with a cobblestone. If you really want to know, I imagined that you had\"},{\"text\":\"something to do with the Thought Police.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"evidently taking this as a\"},{\"text\":\"tribute to the excellence of her disguise.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Not the Thought Police! You didn't honestly think that?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"appearance--merely\"},{\"text\":\"because you're young and fresh and healthy, you understand--I thought that\"},{\"text\":\"probably----'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'You thought I was a good Party member. Pure in word and deed. Banners,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"stuff. And you\"},{\"text\":\"thought that if I had a quarter of a chance I'd denounce you as a\"},{\"text\":\"thought-criminal and get you killed off?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes, something of that kind. A great many young girls are like that,\"},{\"text\":\"you know.'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'It's this bloody thing that does it,' she said, ripping off the scarlet\"},{\"text\":\"sash of the Junior Anti-Sex League and flinging it on to a bough. Then,\"},{\"text\":\"as though touching her waist had reminded her of something, she felt in\"}]","[{\"text\":\"produced a small slab of chocolate. She\"},{\"text\":\"broke it in half and gave one of the pieces to Winston. Even before he had\"},{\"text\":\"taken it he knew by the smell that it was very unusual chocolate. It was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Chocolate normally was\"},{\"text\":\"dull-brown crumbly stuff that tasted, as nearly as one could describe it,\"},{\"text\":\"like the smoke of a rubbish fire. But at some time or another he had tasted\"},{\"text\":\"chocolate like the piece she had given him. The first whiff of its scent\"}]","[{\"text\":\"had stirred up some memory which he could not pin down, but which was\"},{\"text\":\"powerful and troubling.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Where did you get this stuff?' he said.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that sort of girl,\"},{\"text\":\"to look at. I'm good at games. I was a troop-leader in the Spies. I do\"},{\"text\":\"voluntary work three evenings a week for the Junior Anti-Sex League. Hours\"},{\"text\":\"and hours I've spent pasting their bloody rot all over London. I always\"}]","[{\"text\":\"banner in the processions. I always look cheerful and\"},{\"text\":\"I never shirk anything. Always yell with the crowd, that's what I say.\"},{\"text\":\"It's the only way to be safe.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The first fragment of chocolate had melted on Winston's tongue. The taste\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was delightful. But there was still that memory moving round the edges of\"},{\"text\":\"his consciousness, something strongly felt but not reducible to definite\"},{\"text\":\"shape, like an object seen out of the corner of one's eye. He pushed it\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the memory of some action which he\"},{\"text\":\"would have liked to undo but could not.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'You are very young,' he said. 'You are ten or fifteen years younger than\"},{\"text\":\"I am. What could you see to attract you in a man like me?'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'It was something in your face. I thought I'd take a chance. I'm good at\"},{\"text\":\"spotting people who don't belong. As soon as I saw you I knew you were\"},{\"text\":\"against THEM.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"THEM, it appeared, meant the Party, and above all the Inner Party, about\"}]","[{\"text\":\"whom she talked with an open jeering hatred which made Winston feel uneasy,\"},{\"text\":\"although he knew that they were safe here if they could be safe anywhere.\"},{\"text\":\"A thing that astonished him about her was the coarseness of her language.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"swear, and Winston himself very seldom\"},{\"text\":\"did swear, aloud, at any rate. Julia, however, seemed unable to mention\"},{\"text\":\"the Party, and especially the Inner Party, without using the kind of words\"}]","[{\"text\":\"not dislike it. It\"},{\"text\":\"was merely one symptom of her revolt against the Party and all its ways,\"},{\"text\":\"and somehow it seemed natural and healthy, like the sneeze of a horse that\"},{\"text\":\"smells bad hay. They had left the clearing and were wandering again\"}]","[{\"text\":\"chequered shade, with their arms round each other's waists\"},{\"text\":\"whenever it was wide enough to walk two abreast. He noticed how much\"},{\"text\":\"softer her waist seemed to feel now that the sash was gone. They did not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"clearing, Julia said, it was better to\"},{\"text\":\"go quietly. Presently they had reached the edge of the little wood. She\"},{\"text\":\"stopped him.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Don't go out into the open. There might be someone watching. We're all\"}]","[{\"text\":\"behind the boughs.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"They were standing in the shade of hazel bushes. The sunlight, filtering\"},{\"text\":\"through innumerable leaves, was still hot on their faces. Winston looked\"}]","[{\"text\":\"shock of\"},{\"text\":\"recognition. He knew it by sight. An old, close-bitten pasture, with a\"},{\"text\":\"footpath wandering across it and a molehill here and there. In the ragged\"},{\"text\":\"hedge on the opposite side the boughs of the elm trees swayed just\"}]","[{\"text\":\"breeze, and their leaves stirred faintly in dense\"},{\"text\":\"masses like women's hair. Surely somewhere nearby, but out of sight,\"},{\"text\":\"there must be a stream with green pools where dace were swimming?\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"here?' he whispered.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'That's right, there is a stream. It's at the edge of the next field,\"},{\"text\":\"actually. There are fish in it, great big ones. You can watch them lying\"},{\"text\":\"in the pools under the willow trees, waving their tails.'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'It's the Golden Country--almost,' he murmured.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'The Golden Country?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It's nothing, really. A landscape I've seen sometimes in a dream.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Look!' whispered Julia.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"A thrush had alighted on a bough not five metres away, almost at the level\"},{\"text\":\"of their faces. Perhaps it had not seen them. It was in the sun, they in\"},{\"text\":\"the shade. It spread out its wings, fitted them carefully into place\"}]","[{\"text\":\"as though making a sort of obeisance\"},{\"text\":\"to the sun, and then began to pour forth a torrent of song. In the\"},{\"text\":\"afternoon hush the volume of sound was startling. Winston and Julia clung\"},{\"text\":\"together, fascinated. The music went on and on, minute after minute, with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"astonishing variations, never once repeating itself, almost as though the\"},{\"text\":\"bird were deliberately showing off its virtuosity. Sometimes it stopped\"},{\"text\":\"for a few seconds, spread out and resettled its wings, then swelled its\"}]","[{\"text\":\"song. Winston watched it with a sort\"},{\"text\":\"of vague reverence. For whom, for what, was that bird singing? No mate,\"},{\"text\":\"no rival was watching it. What made it sit at the edge of the lonely wood\"},{\"text\":\"and pour its music into nothingness? He wondered whether after all there\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was a microphone hidden somewhere near. He and Julia had spoken only in\"},{\"text\":\"low whispers, and it would not pick up what they had said, but it would\"},{\"text\":\"pick up the thrush. Perhaps at the other end of the instrument some small,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"intently--listening to that. But by degrees\"},{\"text\":\"the flood of music drove all speculations out of his mind. It was as\"},{\"text\":\"though it were a kind of liquid stuff that poured all over him and got\"}]","[{\"text\":\"leaves. He stopped\"},{\"text\":\"thinking and merely felt. The girl's waist in the bend of his arm was soft\"},{\"text\":\"and warm. He pulled her round so that they were breast to breast; her body\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to melt into his. Wherever his hands moved it was all as yielding as\"}]","[{\"text\":\"mouths clung together; it was quite different from the hard\"},{\"text\":\"kisses they had exchanged earlier. When they moved their faces apart again\"},{\"text\":\"both of them sighed deeply. The bird took fright and fled with a clatter\"},{\"text\":\"of wings.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston put his lips against her ear. 'NOW,' he whispered.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Not here,' she whispered back. 'Come back to the hide-out. It's safer.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Quickly, with an occasional crackle of twigs, they threaded their way back\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to the clearing. When they were once inside the ring of saplings she turned\"},{\"text\":\"and faced him. They were both breathing fast, but the smile had reappeared\"},{\"text\":\"round the corners of her mouth. She stood looking at him for an instant,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"overalls. And, yes! it was almost as in his\"},{\"text\":\"dream. Almost as swiftly as he had imagined it, she had torn her clothes\"},{\"text\":\"off, and when she flung them aside it was with that same magnificent\"}]","[{\"text\":\"annihilated. Her body\"},{\"text\":\"gleamed white in the sun. But for a moment he did not look at her body;\"},{\"text\":\"his eyes were anchored by the freckled face with its faint, bold smile.\"},{\"text\":\"He knelt down before her and took her hands in his.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Have you done this before?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Of course. Hundreds of times--well, scores of times, anyway.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'With Party members?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes, always with Party members.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'With members of the Inner Party?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Not with those swine, no. But there's plenty that WOULD if they got half\"},{\"text\":\"a chance. They're not so holy as they make out.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"wished it had been\"},{\"text\":\"hundreds--thousands. Anything that hinted at corruption always filled him\"},{\"text\":\"with a wild hope. Who knew, perhaps the Party was rotten under the surface,\"},{\"text\":\"its cult of strenuousness and self-denial simply a sham concealing\"}]","[{\"text\":\"could have infected the whole lot of them with leprosy or\"},{\"text\":\"syphilis, how gladly he would have done so! Anything to rot, to weaken, to\"},{\"text\":\"undermine! He pulled her down so that they were kneeling face to face.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"men you've had, the more I love you. Do you understand\"},{\"text\":\"that?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Yes, perfectly.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I hate purity, I hate goodness! I don't want any virtue to exist anywhere.\"},{\"text\":\"I want everyone to be corrupt to the bones.'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'Well then, I ought to suit you, dear. I'm corrupt to the bones.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'You like doing this? I don't mean simply me: I mean the thing in itself?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I adore it.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hear. Not merely the love of one\"},{\"text\":\"person but the animal instinct, the simple undifferentiated desire: that\"},{\"text\":\"was the force that would tear the Party to pieces. He pressed her down\"},{\"text\":\"upon the grass, among the fallen bluebells. This time there was no\"}]","[{\"text\":\"difficulty. Presently the rising and falling of their breasts slowed to\"},{\"text\":\"normal speed, and in a sort of pleasant helplessness they fell apart. The\"},{\"text\":\"sun seemed to have grown hotter. They were both sleepy. He reached out for\"}]","[{\"text\":\"them partly over her. Almost immediately\"},{\"text\":\"they fell asleep and slept for about half an hour.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston woke first. He sat up and watched the freckled face, still\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Except for her mouth,\"},{\"text\":\"you could not call her beautiful. There was a line or two round the eyes,\"},{\"text\":\"if you looked closely. The short dark hair was extraordinarily thick and\"},{\"text\":\"soft. It occurred to him that he still did not know her surname or where\"}]","[{\"text\":\"she lived.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The young, strong body, now helpless in sleep, awoke in him a pitying,\"},{\"text\":\"protecting feeling. But the mindless tenderness that he had felt under\"},{\"text\":\"the hazel tree, while the thrush was singing, had not quite come back.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"He pulled the overalls aside and studied her smooth white flank. In the\"},{\"text\":\"old days, he thought, a man looked at a girl's body and saw that it was\"},{\"text\":\"desirable, and that was the end of the story. But you could not have pure\"}]","[{\"text\":\"emotion was pure, because everything was\"},{\"text\":\"mixed up with fear and hatred. Their embrace had been a battle, the climax\"},{\"text\":\"a victory. It was a blow struck against the Party. It was a political act.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Chapter 3\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'We can come here once again,' said Julia. 'It's generally safe to use any\"},{\"text\":\"hide-out twice. But not for another month or two, of course.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"woke up her demeanour had changed. She became alert and\"},{\"text\":\"business-like, put her clothes on, knotted the scarlet sash about her\"},{\"text\":\"waist, and began arranging the details of the journey home. It seemed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"practical cunning which\"},{\"text\":\"Winston lacked, and she seemed also to have an exhaustive knowledge of the\"},{\"text\":\"countryside round London, stored away from innumerable community hikes.\"},{\"text\":\"The route she gave him was quite different from the one by which he had\"}]","[{\"text\":\"come, and brought him out at a different railway station. 'Never go home\"},{\"text\":\"the same way as you went out,' she said, as though enunciating an important\"},{\"text\":\"general principle. She would leave first, and Winston was to wait half an\"},{\"text\":\"hour before following her.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"She had named a place where they could meet after work, four evenings\"},{\"text\":\"hence. It was a street in one of the poorer quarters, where there was an\"},{\"text\":\"open market which was generally crowded and noisy. She would be hanging\"}]","[{\"text\":\"be in search of shoelaces or\"},{\"text\":\"sewing-thread. If she judged that the coast was clear she would blow\"},{\"text\":\"her nose when he approached; otherwise he was to walk past her without\"},{\"text\":\"recognition. But with luck, in the middle of the crowd, it would be\"}]","[{\"text\":\"safe to talk for a quarter of an hour and arrange another meeting.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'And now I must go,' she said as soon as he had mastered his instructions.\"},{\"text\":\"'I'm due back at nineteen-thirty. I've got to put in two hours for the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"League, handing out leaflets, or something. Isn't it\"},{\"text\":\"bloody? Give me a brush-down, would you? Have I got any twigs in my hair?\"},{\"text\":\"Are you sure? Then good-bye, my love, good-bye!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"violently, and a moment\"},{\"text\":\"later pushed her way through the saplings and disappeared into the wood\"},{\"text\":\"with very little noise. Even now he had not found out her surname or her\"},{\"text\":\"address. However, it made no difference, for it was inconceivable that\"}]","[{\"text\":\"they could ever meet indoors or exchange any kind of written communication.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"As it happened, they never went back to the clearing in the wood. During\"},{\"text\":\"the month of May there was only one further occasion on which they actually\"}]","[{\"text\":\"making love. That was in another hiding-place known to Julia,\"},{\"text\":\"the belfry of a ruinous church in an almost-deserted stretch of country\"},{\"text\":\"where an atomic bomb had fallen thirty years earlier. It was a good\"}]","[{\"text\":\"but the getting there was very\"},{\"text\":\"dangerous. For the rest they could meet only in the streets, in a different\"},{\"text\":\"place every evening and never for more than half an hour at a time. In the\"},{\"text\":\"street it was usually possible to talk, after a fashion. As they drifted\"}]","[{\"text\":\"down the crowded pavements, not quite abreast and never looking at one\"},{\"text\":\"another, they carried on a curious, intermittent conversation which flicked\"},{\"text\":\"on and off like the beams of a lighthouse, suddenly nipped into silence\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the proximity of a telescreen, then\"},{\"text\":\"taken up again minutes later in the middle of a sentence, then abruptly\"},{\"text\":\"cut short as they parted at the agreed spot, then continued almost without\"},{\"text\":\"introduction on the following day. Julia appeared to be quite used to this\"}]","[{\"text\":\"kind of conversation, which she called 'talking by instalments'. She was\"},{\"text\":\"also surprisingly adept at speaking without moving her lips. Just once in\"},{\"text\":\"almost a month of nightly meetings they managed to exchange a kiss. They\"}]","[{\"text\":\"side-street (Julia would never speak when\"},{\"text\":\"they were away from the main streets) when there was a deafening roar, the\"},{\"text\":\"earth heaved, and the air darkened, and Winston found himself lying on his\"}]","[{\"text\":\"dropped quite near at\"},{\"text\":\"hand. Suddenly he became aware of Julia's face a few centimetres from his\"},{\"text\":\"own, deathly white, as white as chalk. Even her lips were white. She was\"},{\"text\":\"dead! He clasped her against him and found that he was kissing a live\"}]","[{\"text\":\"warm face. But there was some powdery stuff that got in the way of his\"},{\"text\":\"lips. Both of their faces were thickly coated with plaster.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"There were evenings when they reached their rendezvous and then had to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"another without a sign, because a patrol had just come round\"},{\"text\":\"the corner or a helicopter was hovering overhead. Even if it had been\"},{\"text\":\"less dangerous, it would still have been difficult to find time to meet.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hours, Julia's was even longer, and\"},{\"text\":\"their free days varied according to the pressure of work and did not\"},{\"text\":\"often coincide. Julia, in any case, seldom had an evening completely free.\"},{\"text\":\"She spent an astonishing amount of time in attending lectures and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"demonstrations, distributing literature for the junior Anti-Sex League,\"},{\"text\":\"preparing banners for Hate Week, making collections for the savings\"},{\"text\":\"campaign, and such-like activities. It paid, she said, it was camouflage.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"could break the big ones. She even induced\"},{\"text\":\"Winston to mortgage yet another of his evenings by enrolling himself for\"},{\"text\":\"the part-time munition work which was done voluntarily by zealous Party\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hours of paralysing\"},{\"text\":\"boredom, screwing together small bits of metal which were probably parts\"},{\"text\":\"of bomb fuses, in a draughty, ill-lit workshop where the knocking of\"},{\"text\":\"hammers mingled drearily with the music of the telescreens.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"When they met in the church tower the gaps in their fragmentary\"},{\"text\":\"conversation were filled up. It was a blazing afternoon. The air in the\"},{\"text\":\"little square chamber above the bells was hot and stagnant, and smelt\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sat talking for hours on the dusty,\"},{\"text\":\"twig-littered floor, one or other of them getting up from time to time to\"},{\"text\":\"cast a glance through the arrowslits and make sure that no one was coming.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"with thirty other\"},{\"text\":\"girls ('Always in the stink of women! How I hate women!' she said\"},{\"text\":\"parenthetically), and she worked, as he had guessed, on the novel-writing\"},{\"text\":\"machines in the Fiction Department. She enjoyed her work, which consisted\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and servicing a powerful but tricky electric motor.\"},{\"text\":\"She was 'not clever', but was fond of using her hands and felt at home\"},{\"text\":\"with machinery. She could describe the whole process of composing a novel,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Committee down to the\"},{\"text\":\"final touching-up by the Rewrite Squad. But she was not interested in the\"},{\"text\":\"finished product. She 'didn't much care for reading,' she said. Books were\"},{\"text\":\"just a commodity that had to be produced, like jam or bootlaces.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"She had no memories of anything before the early sixties and the only\"},{\"text\":\"person she had ever known who talked frequently of the days before the\"},{\"text\":\"Revolution was a grandfather who had disappeared when she was eight. At\"}]","[{\"text\":\"hockey team and had won the gymnastics\"},{\"text\":\"trophy two years running. She had been a troop-leader in the Spies and a\"},{\"text\":\"branch secretary in the Youth League before joining the Junior Anti-Sex\"}]","[{\"text\":\"had even (an\"},{\"text\":\"infallible mark of good reputation) been picked out to work in Pornosec,\"},{\"text\":\"the sub-section of the Fiction Department which turned out cheap\"},{\"text\":\"pornography for distribution among the proles. It was nicknamed Muck House\"}]","[{\"text\":\"worked in it, she remarked. There she had remained for\"},{\"text\":\"a year, helping to produce booklets in sealed packets with titles like\"},{\"text\":\"'Spanking Stories' or 'One Night in a Girls' School', to be bought\"}]","[{\"text\":\"impression that they\"},{\"text\":\"were buying something illegal.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What are these books like?' said Winston curiously.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Oh, ghastly rubbish. They're boring, really. They only have six plots,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"round a bit. Of course I was only on the kaleidoscopes.\"},{\"text\":\"I was never in the Rewrite Squad. I'm not literary, dear--not even enough\"},{\"text\":\"for that.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He learned with astonishment that all the workers in Pornosec, except the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"departments, were girls. The theory was that men, whose sex\"},{\"text\":\"instincts were less controllable than those of women, were in greater\"},{\"text\":\"danger of being corrupted by the filth they handled.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"women there,' she added. Girls are\"},{\"text\":\"always supposed to be so pure. Here's one who isn't, anyway.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"She had had her first love-affair when she was sixteen, with a Party member\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'And a good job too,'\"},{\"text\":\"said Julia, 'otherwise they'd have had my name out of him when he\"},{\"text\":\"confessed.' Since then there had been various others. Life as she saw it\"},{\"text\":\"was quite simple. You wanted a good time; 'they', meaning the Party,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"wanted to stop you having it; you broke the rules as best you could. She\"},{\"text\":\"seemed to think it just as natural that 'they' should want to rob you of\"},{\"text\":\"your pleasures as that you should want to avoid being caught. She hated\"}]","[{\"text\":\"words, but she made no general\"},{\"text\":\"criticism of it. Except where it touched upon her own life she had no\"},{\"text\":\"interest in Party doctrine. He noticed that she never used Newspeak words\"},{\"text\":\"except the ones that had passed into everyday use. She had never heard of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the Brotherhood, and refused to believe in its existence. Any kind of\"},{\"text\":\"organized revolt against the Party, which was bound to be a failure,\"},{\"text\":\"struck her as stupid. The clever thing was to break the rules and stay\"}]","[{\"text\":\"vaguely how many others like her there\"},{\"text\":\"might be in the younger generation people who had grown up in the world of\"},{\"text\":\"the Revolution, knowing nothing else, accepting the Party as something\"}]","[{\"text\":\"authority but simply\"},{\"text\":\"evading it, as a rabbit dodges a dog.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"They did not discuss the possibility of getting married. It was too remote\"},{\"text\":\"to be worth thinking about. No imaginable committee would ever sanction\"}]","[{\"text\":\"even if Katharine, Winston's wife, could somehow have been\"},{\"text\":\"got rid of. It was hopeless even as a daydream.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'What was she like, your wife?' said Julia.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"word GOODTHINKFUL? Meaning naturally\"},{\"text\":\"orthodox, incapable of thinking a bad thought?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'No, I didn't know the word, but I know the kind of person, right enough.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"curiously enough\"},{\"text\":\"she appeared to know the essential parts of it already. She described\"},{\"text\":\"to him, almost as though she had seen or felt it, the stiffening of\"},{\"text\":\"Katharine's body as soon as he touched her, the way in which she still\"}]","[{\"text\":\"pushing him from her with all her strength, even when her\"},{\"text\":\"arms were clasped tightly round him. With Julia he felt no difficulty in\"},{\"text\":\"talking about such things: Katharine, in any case, had long ceased to be\"}]","[{\"text\":\"distasteful one.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'I could have stood it if it hadn't been for one thing,' he said. He told\"},{\"text\":\"her about the frigid little ceremony that Katharine had forced him to go\"},{\"text\":\"through on the same night every week. 'She hated it, but nothing would\"}]","[{\"text\":\"make her stop doing it. She used to call it--but you'll never guess.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Our duty to the Party,' said Julia promptly.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'How did you know that?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"talks once a month for the\"},{\"text\":\"over-sixteens. And in the Youth Movement. They rub it into you for years.\"},{\"text\":\"I dare say it works in a lot of cases. But of course you can never tell;\"},{\"text\":\"people are such hypocrites.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"enlarge upon the subject. With Julia, everything came back\"},{\"text