s gave Winston a glance in which there was neither interest nor\"},{\"text\":\"surprise, but only misery. He began walking jerkily up and down, evidently\"}]","[{\"text\":\"unable to keep still. Each time he straightened his pudgy knees it was\"},{\"text\":\"apparent that they were trembling. His eyes had a wide-open, staring look,\"},{\"text\":\"as though he could not prevent himself from gazing at something in the\"},{\"text\":\"middle distance.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"'What are you in for?' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Thoughtcrime!' said Parsons, almost blubbering. The tone of his voice\"},{\"text\":\"implied at once a complete admission of his guilt and a sort of incredulous\"}]","[{\"text\":\"paused opposite\"},{\"text\":\"Winston and began eagerly appealing to him: 'You don't think they'll shoot\"},{\"text\":\"me, do you, old chap? They don't shoot you if you haven't actually done\"},{\"text\":\"anything--only thoughts, which you can't help? I know they give you a fair\"}]","[{\"text\":\"trust them for that! They'll know my record, won't they?\"},{\"text\":\"YOU know what kind of chap I was. Not a bad chap in my way. Not brainy, of\"},{\"text\":\"course, but keen. I tried to do my best for the Party, didn't I? I'll get\"}]","[{\"text\":\"A chap like me\"},{\"text\":\"could make himself pretty useful in a labour-camp. They wouldn't shoot me\"},{\"text\":\"for going off the rails just once?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Are you guilty?' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"glance at the\"},{\"text\":\"telescreen. 'You don't think the Party would arrest an innocent man,\"},{\"text\":\"do you?' His frog-like face grew calmer, and even took on a slightly\"},{\"text\":\"sanctimonious expression. 'Thoughtcrime is a dreadful thing, old man,'\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sententiously. 'It's insidious. It can get hold of you without\"},{\"text\":\"your even knowing it. Do you know how it got hold of me? In my sleep! Yes,\"},{\"text\":\"that's a fact. There I was, working away, trying to do my bit--never knew\"}]","[{\"text\":\"all. And then I started talking in my\"},{\"text\":\"sleep. Do you know what they heard me saying?'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He sank his voice, like someone who is obliged for medical reasons to\"},{\"text\":\"utter an obscenity.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Brother!\\\" Yes, I said that! Said it over and over again,\"},{\"text\":\"it seems. Between you and me, old man, I'm glad they got me before it went\"},{\"text\":\"any further. Do you know what I'm going to say to them when I go up before\"}]","[{\"text\":\"for saving me\"},{\"text\":\"before it was too late.\\\"'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Who denounced you?' said Winston.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'It was my little daughter,' said Parsons with a sort of doleful pride.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and nipped off to\"},{\"text\":\"the patrols the very next day. Pretty smart for a nipper of seven, eh?\"},{\"text\":\"I don't bear her any grudge for it. In fact I'm proud of her. It shows I\"},{\"text\":\"brought her up in the right spirit, anyway.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"jerky movements up and down, several times, casting a\"},{\"text\":\"longing glance at the lavatory pan. Then he suddenly ripped down his\"},{\"text\":\"shorts.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Excuse me, old man,' he said. 'I can't help it. It's the waiting.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"He plumped his large posterior into the lavatory pan. Winston covered his\"},{\"text\":\"face with his hands.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Smith!' yelled the voice from the telescreen. '6079 Smith W.! Uncover your\"},{\"text\":\"face. No faces covered in the cells.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston uncovered his face. Parsons used the lavatory, loudly and\"},{\"text\":\"abundantly. It then turned out that the plug was defective and the cell\"},{\"text\":\"stank abominably for hours afterwards.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"came and went, mysteriously. One, a\"},{\"text\":\"woman, was consigned to 'Room 101', and, Winston noticed, seemed to shrivel\"},{\"text\":\"and turn a different colour when she heard the words. A time came when, if\"},{\"text\":\"it had been morning when he was brought here, it would be afternoon; or if\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it had been afternoon, then it would be midnight. There were six prisoners\"},{\"text\":\"in the cell, men and women. All sat very still. Opposite Winston there sat\"},{\"text\":\"a man with a chinless, toothy face exactly like that of some large,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"cheeks were so pouched at the bottom\"},{\"text\":\"that it was difficult not to believe that he had little stores of food\"},{\"text\":\"tucked away there. His pale-grey eyes flitted timorously from face to face\"},{\"text\":\"and turned quickly away again when he caught anyone's eye.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The door opened, and another prisoner was brought in whose appearance sent\"},{\"text\":\"a momentary chill through Winston. He was a commonplace, mean-looking man\"},{\"text\":\"who might have been an engineer or technician of some kind. But what was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"face. It was like a skull. Because of\"},{\"text\":\"its thinness the mouth and eyes looked disproportionately large, and the\"},{\"text\":\"eyes seemed filled with a murderous, unappeasable hatred of somebody or\"},{\"text\":\"something.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"little distance from Winston. Winston\"},{\"text\":\"did not look at him again, but the tormented, skull-like face was as\"},{\"text\":\"vivid in his mind as though it had been straight in front of his eyes.\"},{\"text\":\"Suddenly he realized what was the matter. The man was dying of starvation.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The same thought seemed to occur almost simultaneously to everyone in the\"},{\"text\":\"cell. There was a very faint stirring all the way round the bench. The\"},{\"text\":\"eyes of the chinless man kept flitting towards the skull-faced man, then\"}]","[{\"text\":\"dragged back by an irresistible\"},{\"text\":\"attraction. Presently he began to fidget on his seat. At last he stood up,\"},{\"text\":\"waddled clumsily across the cell, dug down into the pocket of his overalls,\"},{\"text\":\"and, with an abashed air, held out a grimy piece of bread to the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"skull-faced man.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"There was a furious, deafening roar from the telescreen. The chinless man\"},{\"text\":\"jumped in his tracks. The skull-faced man had quickly thrust his hands\"},{\"text\":\"behind his back, as though demonstrating to all the world that he refused\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the gift.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Bumstead!' roared the voice. '2713 Bumstead J.! Let fall that piece of\"},{\"text\":\"bread!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The chinless man dropped the piece of bread on the floor.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"where you are,' said the voice. 'Face the door. Make no\"},{\"text\":\"movement.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The chinless man obeyed. His large pouchy cheeks were quivering\"},{\"text\":\"uncontrollably. The door clanged open. As the young officer entered and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"there emerged from behind him a short stumpy guard with\"},{\"text\":\"enormous arms and shoulders. He took his stand opposite the chinless man,\"},{\"text\":\"and then, at a signal from the officer, let free a frightful blow, with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"chinless man's mouth.\"},{\"text\":\"The force of it seemed almost to knock him clear of the floor. His body\"},{\"text\":\"was flung across the cell and fetched up against the base of the lavatory\"},{\"text\":\"seat. For a moment he lay as though stunned, with dark blood oozing from\"}]","[{\"text\":\"his mouth and nose. A very faint whimpering or squeaking, which seemed\"},{\"text\":\"unconscious, came out of him. Then he rolled over and raised himself\"},{\"text\":\"unsteadily on hands and knees. Amid a stream of blood and saliva, the two\"}]","[{\"text\":\"his mouth.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The prisoners sat very still, their hands crossed on their knees. The\"},{\"text\":\"chinless man climbed back into his place. Down one side of his face the\"},{\"text\":\"flesh was darkening. His mouth had swollen into a shapeless cherry-coloured\"}]","[{\"text\":\"mass with a black hole in the middle of it.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"From time to time a little blood dripped on to the breast of his overalls.\"},{\"text\":\"His grey eyes still flitted from face to face, more guiltily than ever,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"how much the others despised him for\"},{\"text\":\"his humiliation.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The door opened. With a small gesture the officer indicated the\"},{\"text\":\"skull-faced man.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Room 101,' he said.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and a flurry at Winston's side. The man had actually\"},{\"text\":\"flung himself on his knees on the floor, with his hand clasped together.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Comrade! Officer!' he cried. 'You don't have to take me to that place!\"}]","[{\"text\":\"already? What else is it you want to know?\"},{\"text\":\"There's nothing I wouldn't confess, nothing! Just tell me what it is and\"},{\"text\":\"I'll confess straight off. Write it down and I'll sign it--anything!\"},{\"text\":\"Not room 101!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the officer.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The man's face, already very pale, turned a colour Winston would not have\"},{\"text\":\"believed possible. It was definitely, unmistakably, a shade of green.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"for weeks. Finish\"},{\"text\":\"it off and let me die. Shoot me. Hang me. Sentence me to twenty-five\"},{\"text\":\"years. Is there somebody else you want me to give away? Just say who it is\"},{\"text\":\"and I'll tell you anything you want. I don't care who it is or what you do\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a wife and three children. The biggest of them isn't six\"},{\"text\":\"years old. You can take the whole lot of them and cut their throats in\"},{\"text\":\"front of my eyes, and I'll stand by and watch it. But not Room 101!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Room 101,' said the officer.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The man looked frantically round at the other prisoners, as though with\"},{\"text\":\"some idea that he could put another victim in his own place. His eyes\"},{\"text\":\"settled on the smashed face of the chinless man. He flung out a lean arm.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"you ought to be taking, not me!' he shouted. 'You didn't\"},{\"text\":\"hear what he was saying after they bashed his face. Give me a chance and\"},{\"text\":\"I'll tell you every word of it. HE'S the one that's against the Party, not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a shriek. 'You\"},{\"text\":\"didn't hear him!' he repeated. 'Something went wrong with the telescreen.\"},{\"text\":\"HE'S the one you want. Take him, not me!'\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The two sturdy guards had stooped to take him by the arms. But just at\"}]","[{\"text\":\"flung himself across the floor of the cell and grabbed one\"},{\"text\":\"of the iron legs that supported the bench. He had set up a wordless\"},{\"text\":\"howling, like an animal. The guards took hold of him to wrench him loose,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"strength. For perhaps twenty seconds\"},{\"text\":\"they were hauling at him. The prisoners sat quiet, their hands crossed on\"},{\"text\":\"their knees, looking straight in front of them. The howling stopped; the\"},{\"text\":\"man had no breath left for anything except hanging on. Then there was a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"different kind of cry. A kick from a guard's boot had broken the fingers\"},{\"text\":\"of one of his hands. They dragged him to his feet.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'Room 101,' said the officer.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sunken, nursing his\"},{\"text\":\"crushed hand, all the fight had gone out of him.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"A long time passed. If it had been midnight when the skull-faced man was\"},{\"text\":\"taken away, it was morning: if morning, it was afternoon. Winston was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"alone, and had been alone for hours. The pain of sitting on the narrow\"},{\"text\":\"bench was such that often he got up and walked about, unreproved by the\"},{\"text\":\"telescreen. The piece of bread still lay where the chinless man had\"}]","[{\"text\":\"needed a hard effort not to look at it,\"},{\"text\":\"but presently hunger gave way to thirst. His mouth was sticky and\"},{\"text\":\"evil-tasting. The humming sound and the unvarying white light induced a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"would get up\"},{\"text\":\"because the ache in his bones was no longer bearable, and then would sit\"},{\"text\":\"down again almost at once because he was too dizzy to make sure of\"},{\"text\":\"staying on his feet. Whenever his physical sensations were a little under\"}]","[{\"text\":\"returned. Sometimes with a fading hope he thought of\"},{\"text\":\"O'Brien and the razor blade. It was thinkable that the razor blade might\"},{\"text\":\"arrive concealed in his food, if he were ever fed. More dimly he thought\"}]","[{\"text\":\"far worse than he.\"},{\"text\":\"She might be screaming with pain at this moment. He thought: 'If I could\"},{\"text\":\"save Julia by doubling my own pain, would I do it? Yes, I would.' But that\"},{\"text\":\"was merely an intellectual decision, taken because he knew that he ought\"}]","[{\"text\":\"not feel it. In this place you could not feel anything,\"},{\"text\":\"except pain and foreknowledge of pain. Besides, was it possible, when you\"},{\"text\":\"were actually suffering it, to wish for any reason that your own pain\"}]","[{\"text\":\"yet.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The boots were approaching again. The door opened. O'Brien came in.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Winston started to his feet. The shock of the sight had driven all\"}]","[{\"text\":\"forgot the\"},{\"text\":\"presence of the telescreen.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'They've got you too!' he cried.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'They got me a long time ago,' said O'Brien with a mild, almost regretful\"}]","[{\"text\":\"broad-chested\"},{\"text\":\"guard with a long black truncheon in his hand.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"'You know this, Winston,' said O'Brien. 'Don't deceive yourself. You did\"},{\"text\":\"know it--you have always known it.'\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it. But there was no time to think of\"},{\"text\":\"that. All he had eyes for was the truncheon in the guard's hand. It might\"},{\"text\":\"fall anywhere; on the crown, on the tip of the ear, on the upper arm, on\"},{\"text\":\"the elbow----\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"knees, almost paralysed, clasping the\"},{\"text\":\"stricken elbow with his other hand. Everything had exploded into yellow\"},{\"text\":\"light. Inconceivable, inconceivable that one blow could cause such pain!\"},{\"text\":\"The light cleared and he could see the other two looking down at him. The\"}]","[{\"text\":\"guard was laughing at his contortions. One question at any rate was\"},{\"text\":\"answered. Never, for any reason on earth, could you wish for an increase\"},{\"text\":\"of pain. Of pain you could wish only one thing: that it should stop.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"physical pain. In the face of pain\"},{\"text\":\"there are no heroes, no heroes, he thought over and over as he writhed\"},{\"text\":\"on the floor, clutching uselessly at his disabled left arm.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Chapter 2\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He was lying on something that felt like a camp bed, except that it was\"},{\"text\":\"higher off the ground and that he was fixed down in some way so that he\"}]","[{\"text\":\"stronger than usual was falling on his\"},{\"text\":\"face. O'Brien was standing at his side, looking down at him intently. At\"},{\"text\":\"the other side of him stood a man in a white coat, holding a hypodermic\"},{\"text\":\"syringe.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"eyes were open he took in his surroundings only gradually.\"},{\"text\":\"He had the impression of swimming up into this room from some quite\"},{\"text\":\"different world, a sort of underwater world far beneath it. How long he\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Since the moment when they arrested\"},{\"text\":\"him he had not seen darkness or daylight. Besides, his memories were not\"},{\"text\":\"continuous. There had been times when consciousness, even the sort of\"},{\"text\":\"consciousness that one has in sleep, had stopped dead and started again\"}]","[{\"text\":\"after a blank interval. But whether the intervals were of days or weeks\"},{\"text\":\"or only seconds, there was no way of knowing.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"With that first blow on the elbow the nightmare had started. Later he was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"happened was merely a preliminary, a routine\"},{\"text\":\"interrogation to which nearly all prisoners were subjected. There was a\"},{\"text\":\"long range of crimes--espionage, sabotage, and the like--to which everyone\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a formality,\"},{\"text\":\"though the torture was real. How many times he had been beaten, how long\"},{\"text\":\"the beatings had continued, he could not remember. Always there were five\"},{\"text\":\"or six men in black uniforms at him simultaneously. Sometimes it was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it was truncheons, sometimes it was steel rods, sometimes\"},{\"text\":\"it was boots. There were times when he rolled about the floor, as shameless\"},{\"text\":\"as an animal, writhing his body this way and that in an endless, hopeless\"}]","[{\"text\":\"inviting more and yet more kicks,\"},{\"text\":\"in his ribs, in his belly, on his elbows, on his shins, in his groin,\"},{\"text\":\"in his testicles, on the bone at the base of his spine. There were times\"},{\"text\":\"when it went on and on until the cruel, wicked, unforgivable thing seemed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"to him not that the guards continued to beat him but that he could not\"},{\"text\":\"force himself into losing consciousness. There were times when his nerve\"},{\"text\":\"so forsook him that he began shouting for mercy even before the beating\"}]","[{\"text\":\"drawn back for a blow was enough\"},{\"text\":\"to make him pour forth a confession of real and imaginary crimes. There\"},{\"text\":\"were other times when he started out with the resolve of confessing\"},{\"text\":\"nothing, when every word had to be forced out of him between gasps of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"pain, and there were times when he feebly tried to compromise, when he\"},{\"text\":\"said to himself: 'I will confess, but not yet. I must hold out till the\"},{\"text\":\"pain becomes unbearable. Three more kicks, two more kicks, and then I will\"}]","[{\"text\":\"he was beaten till he could hardly\"},{\"text\":\"stand, then flung like a sack of potatoes on to the stone floor of a cell,\"},{\"text\":\"left to recuperate for a few hours, and then taken out and beaten again.\"},{\"text\":\"There were also longer periods of recovery. He remembered them dimly,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"because they were spent chiefly in sleep or stupor. He remembered a cell\"},{\"text\":\"with a plank bed, a sort of shelf sticking out from the wall, and a tin\"},{\"text\":\"wash-basin, and meals of hot soup and bread and sometimes coffee. He\"}]","[{\"text\":\"scrape his chin and crop his hair,\"},{\"text\":\"and businesslike, unsympathetic men in white coats feeling his pulse,\"},{\"text\":\"tapping his reflexes, turning up his eyelids, running harsh fingers over\"},{\"text\":\"him in search for broken bones, and shooting needles into his arm to make\"}]","[{\"text\":\"him sleep.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The beatings grew less frequent, and became mainly a threat, a horror\"},{\"text\":\"to which he could be sent back at any moment when his answers were\"},{\"t