om of the two\"}]","[{\"text\":\"dark, cramped bedroom became unbearable. Winston whined\"},{\"text\":\"and grizzled, made futile demands for food, fretted about the room pulling\"},{\"text\":\"everything out of place and kicking the wainscoting until the neighbours\"}]","[{\"text\":\"intermittently. In the\"},{\"text\":\"end his mother said, 'Now be good, and I'll buy you a toy. A lovely\"},{\"text\":\"toy--you'll love it'; and then she had gone out in the rain, to a little\"},{\"text\":\"general shop which was still sporadically open nearby, and came back with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a cardboard box containing an outfit of Snakes and Ladders. He could still\"},{\"text\":\"remember the smell of the damp cardboard. It was a miserable outfit. The\"},{\"text\":\"board was cracked and the tiny wooden dice were so ill-cut that they\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Winston looked at the thing sulkily and\"},{\"text\":\"without interest. But then his mother lit a piece of candle and they sat\"},{\"text\":\"down on the floor to play. Soon he was wildly excited and shouting with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ladders and then\"},{\"text\":\"came slithering down the snakes again, almost to the starting-point. They\"},{\"text\":\"played eight games, winning four each. His tiny sister, too young to\"},{\"text\":\"understand what the game was about, had sat propped up against a bolster,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the others were laughing. For a whole afternoon they had\"},{\"text\":\"all been happy together, as in his earlier childhood.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He pushed the picture out of his mind. It was a false memory. He was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"matter so long as\"},{\"text\":\"one knew them for what they were. Some things had happened, others had not\"},{\"text\":\"happened. He turned back to the chessboard and picked up the white knight\"},{\"text\":\"again. Almost in the same instant it dropped on to the board with a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"started as though a pin had run into him.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\"