t the final, indispensable, healing change had never happened,\"},{\"text\":\"until this moment.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"still pouring forth its tale of prisoners\"},{\"text\":\"and booty and slaughter, but the shouting outside had died down a little.\"},{\"text\":\"The waiters were turning back to their work. One of them approached with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"paid no attention\"},{\"text\":\"as his glass was filled up. He was not running or cheering any longer. He\"},{\"text\":\"was back in the Ministry of Love, with everything forgiven, his soul white\"},{\"text\":\"as snow. He was in the public dock, confessing everything, implicating\"}]","[{\"text\":\"walking down the white-tiled corridor, with the feeling\"},{\"text\":\"of walking in sunlight, and an armed guard at his back. The long-hoped-for\"},{\"text\":\"bullet was entering his brain.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"He gazed up at the enormous face. Forty years it had taken him to learn\"}]","[{\"text\":\"what kind of smile was hidden beneath the dark moustache. O cruel, needless\"},{\"text\":\"misunderstanding! O stubborn, self-willed exile from the loving breast!\"},{\"text\":\"Two gin-scented tears trickled down the sides of his nose. But it was all\"}]","[{\"text\":\"struggle was finished. He had won\"},{\"text\":\"the victory over himself. He loved Big Brother.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"THE END\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"APPENDIX.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The Principles of Newspeak\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Newspeak was the official language of Oceania and had been devised to meet\"},{\"text\":\"the ideological needs of Ingsoc, or English Socialism. In the year 1984\"}]","[{\"text\":\"yet anyone who used Newspeak as his sole means of\"},{\"text\":\"communication, either in speech or writing. The leading articles in\"},{\"text\":\"'The Times' were written in it, but this was a TOUR DE FORCE which could\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that Newspeak would\"},{\"text\":\"have finally superseded Oldspeak (or Standard English, as we should\"},{\"text\":\"call it) by about the year 2050. Meanwhile it gained ground steadily, all\"},{\"text\":\"Party members tending to use Newspeak words and grammatical constructions\"}]","[{\"text\":\"more and more in their everyday speech. The version in use in 1984, and\"},{\"text\":\"embodied in the Ninth and Tenth Editions of the Newspeak Dictionary, was\"},{\"text\":\"a provisional one, and contained many superfluous words and archaic\"}]","[{\"text\":\"suppressed later. It is with the final,\"},{\"text\":\"perfected version, as embodied in the Eleventh Edition of the Dictionary,\"},{\"text\":\"that we are concerned here.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The purpose of Newspeak was not only to provide a medium of expression\"}]","[{\"text\":\"for the world-view and mental habits proper to the devotees of Ingsoc,\"},{\"text\":\"but to make all other modes of thought impossible. It was intended that\"},{\"text\":\"when Newspeak had been adopted once and for all and Oldspeak forgotten,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"thought diverging from the principles of\"},{\"text\":\"Ingsoc--should be literally unthinkable, at least so far as thought is\"},{\"text\":\"dependent on words. Its vocabulary was so constructed as to give exact and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Party member could\"},{\"text\":\"properly wish to express, while excluding all other meanings and also the\"},{\"text\":\"possibility of arriving at them by indirect methods. This was done partly\"},{\"text\":\"by the invention of new words, but chiefly by eliminating undesirable\"}]","[{\"text\":\"stripping such words as remained of unorthodox meanings, and\"},{\"text\":\"so far as possible of all secondary meanings whatever. To give a single\"},{\"text\":\"example. The word FREE still existed in Newspeak, but it could only be\"}]","[{\"text\":\"is free from lice' or 'This field is\"},{\"text\":\"free from weeds'. It could not be used in its old sense of 'politically\"},{\"text\":\"free' or 'intellectually free' since political and intellectual freedom no\"},{\"text\":\"longer existed even as concepts, and were therefore of necessity nameless.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Quite apart from the suppression of definitely heretical words, reduction\"},{\"text\":\"of vocabulary was regarded as an end in itself, and no word that could be\"},{\"text\":\"dispensed with was allowed to survive. Newspeak was designed not to extend\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and this purpose was indirectly\"},{\"text\":\"assisted by cutting the choice of words down to a minimum.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"Newspeak was founded on the English language as we now know it, though\"}]","[{\"text\":\"newly-created words,\"},{\"text\":\"would be barely intelligible to an English-speaker of our own day. Newspeak\"},{\"text\":\"words were divided into three distinct classes, known as the A vocabulary,\"},{\"text\":\"the B vocabulary (also called compound words), and the C vocabulary.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"It will be simpler to discuss each class separately, but the grammatical\"},{\"text\":\"peculiarities of the language can be dealt with in the section devoted to\"},{\"text\":\"the A vocabulary, since the same rules held good for all three categories.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"THE A VOCABULARY. The A vocabulary consisted of the words needed for the\"},{\"text\":\"business of everyday life--for such things as eating, drinking, working,\"},{\"text\":\"putting on one's clothes, going up and down stairs, riding in vehicles,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was composed almost entirely of words\"},{\"text\":\"that we already possess words like HIT, RUN, DOG, TREE, SUGAR, HOUSE,\"},{\"text\":\"FIELD--but in comparison with the present-day English vocabulary their\"},{\"text\":\"number was extremely small, while their meanings were far more rigidly\"}]","[{\"text\":\"defined. All ambiguities and shades of meaning had been purged out of\"},{\"text\":\"them. So far as it could be achieved, a Newspeak word of this class was\"},{\"text\":\"simply a staccato sound expressing ONE clearly understood concept. It\"}]","[{\"text\":\"use the A vocabulary for literary\"},{\"text\":\"purposes or for political or philosophical discussion. It was intended\"},{\"text\":\"only to express simple, purposive thoughts, usually involving concrete\"},{\"text\":\"objects or physical actions.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"Newspeak had two outstanding peculiarities. The first of\"},{\"text\":\"these was an almost complete interchangeability between different parts of\"},{\"text\":\"speech. Any word in the language (in principle this applied even to very\"}]","[{\"text\":\"as verb, noun,\"},{\"text\":\"adjective, or adverb. Between the verb and the noun form, when they were\"},{\"text\":\"of the same root, there was never any variation, this rule of itself\"},{\"text\":\"involving the destruction of many archaic forms. The word THOUGHT, for\"}]","[{\"text\":\"exist in Newspeak. Its place was taken by THINK, which\"},{\"text\":\"did duty for both noun and verb. No etymological principle was followed\"},{\"text\":\"here: in some cases it was the original noun that was chosen for retention,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"kindred meaning\"},{\"text\":\"were not etymologically connected, one or other of them was frequently\"},{\"text\":\"suppressed. There was, for example, no such word as CUT, its meaning being\"},{\"text\":\"sufficiently covered by the noun-verb KNIFE. Adjectives were formed by\"}]","[{\"text\":\"-FUL to the noun-verb, and adverbs by adding -WISE. Thus\"},{\"text\":\"for example, SPEEDFUL meant 'rapid' and SPEEDWISE meant 'quickly'. Certain\"},{\"text\":\"of our present-day adjectives, such as GOOD, STRONG, BIG, BLACK, SOFT,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"There was little\"},{\"text\":\"need for them, since almost any adjectival meaning could be arrived at by\"},{\"text\":\"adding -FUL to a noun-verb. None of the now-existing adverbs was retained,\"},{\"text\":\"except for a very few already ending in -WISE: the -WISE termination was\"}]","[{\"text\":\"word WELL, for example, was replaced by GOODWISE.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"In addition, any word--this again applied in principle to every word in\"},{\"text\":\"the language--could be negatived by adding the affix UN-, or could be\"}]","[{\"text\":\"for still greater emphasis,\"},{\"text\":\"DOUBLEPLUS-. Thus, for example, UNCOLD meant 'warm', while PLUSCOLD and\"},{\"text\":\"DOUBLEPLUSCOLD meant, respectively, 'very cold' and 'superlatively cold'.\"},{\"text\":\"It was also possible, as in present-day English, to modify the meaning of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"almost any word by prepositional affixes such as ANTE-, POST-, UP-, DOWN-,\"},{\"text\":\"etc. By such methods it was found possible to bring about an enormous\"},{\"text\":\"diminution of vocabulary. Given, for instance, the word GOOD, there was no\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the required meaning was equally\"},{\"text\":\"well--indeed, better--expressed by UNGOOD. All that was necessary, in any\"},{\"text\":\"case where two words formed a natural pair of opposites, was to decide\"},{\"text\":\"which of them to suppress. DARK, for example, could be replaced by UNLIGHT,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"or LIGHT by UNDARK, according to preference.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The second distinguishing mark of Newspeak grammar was its regularity.\"},{\"text\":\"Subject to a few exceptions which are mentioned below all inflexions\"}]","[{\"text\":\"verbs the preterite and the past\"},{\"text\":\"participle were the same and ended in -ED. The preterite of STEAL was\"},{\"text\":\"STEALED, the preterite of THINK was THINKED, and so on throughout the\"},{\"text\":\"language, all such forms as SWAM, GAVE, BROUGHT, SPOKE, TAKEN, etc., being\"}]","[{\"text\":\"abolished. All plurals were made by adding -S or -ES as the case might be.\"},{\"text\":\"The plurals OF MAN, OX, LIFE, were MANS, OXES, LIFES. Comparison of\"},{\"text\":\"adjectives was invariably made by adding -ER, -EST (GOOD, GOODER, GOODEST),\"}]","[{\"text\":\"formation being suppressed.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The only classes of words that were still allowed to inflect irregularly\"},{\"text\":\"were the pronouns, the relatives, the demonstrative adjectives, and the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"usage, except that\"},{\"text\":\"WHOM had been scrapped as unnecessary, and the SHALL, SHOULD tenses had\"},{\"text\":\"been dropped, all their uses being covered by WILL and WOULD. There were\"},{\"text\":\"also certain irregularities in word-formation arising out of the need for\"}]","[{\"text\":\"speech. A word which was difficult to utter, or was liable\"},{\"text\":\"to be incorrectly heard, was held to be ipso facto a bad word; occasionally\"},{\"text\":\"therefore, for the sake of euphony, extra letters were inserted into a word\"}]","[{\"text\":\"But this need made itself felt\"},{\"text\":\"chiefly in connexion with the B vocabulary. WHY so great an importance was\"},{\"text\":\"attached to ease of pronunciation will be made clear later in this essay.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"consisted of words which had been\"},{\"text\":\"deliberately constructed for political purposes: words, that is to say,\"},{\"text\":\"which not only had in every case a political implication, but were intended\"},{\"text\":\"to impose a desirable mental attitude upon the person using them. Without\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a full understanding of the principles of Ingsoc it was difficult to use\"},{\"text\":\"these words correctly. In some cases they could be translated into\"},{\"text\":\"Oldspeak, or even into words taken from the A vocabulary, but this usually\"}]","[{\"text\":\"involved the loss of certain\"},{\"text\":\"overtones. The B words were a sort of verbal shorthand, often packing\"},{\"text\":\"whole ranges of ideas into a few syllables, and at the same time more\"},{\"text\":\"accurate and forcible than ordinary language.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"The B words were in all cases compound words. [Compound words such as\"},{\"text\":\"SPEAKWRITE, were of course to be found in the A vocabulary, but these were\"},{\"text\":\"merely convenient abbreviations and had no special ideological colour.]\"}]","[{\"text\":\"or portions of words, welded together\"},{\"text\":\"in an easily pronounceable form. The resulting amalgam was always a\"},{\"text\":\"noun-verb, and inflected according to the ordinary rules. To take a single\"},{\"text\":\"example: the word GOODTHINK, meaning, very roughly, 'orthodoxy', or, if\"}]","[{\"text\":\"one chose to regard it as a verb, 'to think in an orthodox manner'. This\"},{\"text\":\"inflected as follows: noun-verb, GOODTHINK; past tense and past participle,\"},{\"text\":\"GOODTHINKED; present participle, GOOD-THINKING; adjective, GOODTHINKFUL;\"}]","[{\"text\":\"GOODTHINKER.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"The B words were not constructed on any etymological plan. The words of\"},{\"text\":\"which they were made up could be any parts of speech, and could be placed\"},{\"text\":\"in any order and mutilated in any way which made them easy to pronounce\"}]","[{\"text\":\"while indicating their derivation. In the word CRIMETHINK (thoughtcrime),\"},{\"text\":\"for instance, the THINK came second, whereas in THINKPOL (Thought Police)\"},{\"text\":\"it came first, and in the latter word POLICE had lost its second syllable.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"securing euphony, irregular formations\"},{\"text\":\"were commoner in the B vocabulary than in the A vocabulary. For example,\"},{\"text\":\"the adjective forms of MINITRUE, MINIPAX, and MINILUV were, respectively,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"because -TRUEFUL,\"},{\"text\":\"-PAXFUL, and -LOVEFUL were slightly awkward to pronounce. In principle,\"},{\"text\":\"however, all B words could inflect, and all inflected in exactly the\"},{\"text\":\"same way.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"barely intelligible to\"},{\"text\":\"anyone who had not mastered the language as a whole. Consider, for example,\"},{\"text\":\"such a typical sentence from a 'Times' leading article as OLDTHINKERS\"},{\"text\":\"UNBELLYFEEL INGSOC. The shortest rendering that one could make of this\"}]","[{\"text\":\"in Oldspeak would be: 'Those whose ideas were formed before the Revolution\"},{\"text\":\"cannot have a full emotional understanding of the principles of English\"},{\"text\":\"Socialism.' But this is not an adequate translation. To begin with, in\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the Newspeak sentence quoted above,\"},{\"text\":\"one would have to have a clear idea of what is meant by INGSOC. And in\"},{\"text\":\"addition, only a person thoroughly grounded in Ingsoc could appreciate\"},{\"text\":\"the full force of the word BELLYFEEL, which implied a blind, enthusiastic\"}]","[{\"text\":\"acceptance difficult to imagine today; or of the word OLDTHINK, which was\"},{\"text\":\"inextricably mixed up with the idea of wickedness and decadence. But the\"},{\"text\":\"special function of certain Newspeak words, of which OLDTHINK was one,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"as to destroy them. These words,\"},{\"text\":\"necessarily few in number, had had their meanings extended until they\"},{\"text\":\"contained within themselves whole batteries of words which, as they were\"},{\"text\":\"sufficiently covered by a single comprehensive term, could now be scrapped\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and forgotten. The greatest difficulty facing the compilers of the Newspeak\"},{\"text\":\"Dictionary was not to invent new words, but, having invented them, to make\"},{\"text\":\"sure what they meant: to make sure, that is to say, what ranges of words\"},{\"text\":\"they cancelled by their existence.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"As we have already seen in the case of the word FREE, words which had\"},{\"text\":\"once borne a heretical meaning were sometimes retained for the sake of\"},{\"text\":\"convenience, but only with the undesirable meanings purged out of them.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"JUSTICE, MORALITY, INTERNATIONALISM,\"},{\"text\":\"DEMOCRACY, SCIENCE, and RELIGION had simply ceased to exist. A few blanket\"},{\"text\":\"words covered them, and, in covering them, abolished them. All words\"},{\"text\":\"grouping themselves round the concepts of liberty and equality, for\"}]","[{\"text\":\"instance, were contained in the single word CRIMETHINK, while all words\"},{\"text\":\"grouping themselves round the concepts of objectivity and rationalism\"},{\"text\":\"were contained in the single word OLDTHINK. Greater precision would have\"}]","[{\"text\":\"a Party member was an outlook similar\"},{\"text\":\"to that of the ancient Hebrew who knew, without knowing much else, that\"},{\"text\":\"all nations other than his own worshipped 'false gods'. He did not need to\"},{\"text\":\"know that these gods were called Baal, Osiris, Moloch, Ashtaroth, and the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"like: probably the less he knew about them the better for his orthodoxy.\"},{\"text\":\"He knew Jehovah and the commandments of Jehovah: he knew, therefore, that\"},{\"text\":\"all gods with other names or other attributes were false gods. In somewhat\"}]","[{\"text\":\"what constituted right conduct, and in\"},{\"text\":\"exceedingly vague, generalized terms he knew what kinds of departure from\"},{\"text\":\"it were possible. His sexual life, for example, was entirely regulated by\"}]","[{\"text\":\"GOODSEX (chastity).\"},{\"text\":\"SEXCRIME covered all sexual misdeeds whatever. It covered fornication,\"},{\"text\":\"adultery, homosexuality, and other perversions, and, in addition, normal\"},{\"text\":\"intercourse practised for its own sake. There was no need to enumerate\"}]","[{\"text\":\"them separately, since they were all equally culpable, and, in principle,\"},{\"text\":\"all punishable by death. In the C vocabulary, which consisted of scientific\"},{\"text\":\"and technical words, it might be necessary to give specialized names to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ordinary citizen had no need of them.\"},{\"text\":\"He knew what was meant by GOODSEX--that is to say, normal intercourse\"},{\"text\":\"between man and wife, for the sole purpose of begetting children, and\"},{\"text\":\"without physical pleasure on the part of the woman: all else was SEXCRIME.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"In Newspeak it was seldom possible to follow a heretical thought further\"},{\"text\":\"than the perception that it WAS heretical: beyond that point the necessary\"},{\"text\":\"words were nonexistent.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"great many were\"},{\"text\":\"euphemisms. Such words, for instance, as JOYCAMP (forced-labour camp) or\"},{\"text\":\"MINIPAX (Ministry of Peace, i.e. Ministry of War) meant almost the exact\"},{\"text\":\"opposite of what they appeared to mean. Some words, on the other hand,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and contemptuous understanding of the real nature of\"},{\"text\":\"Oceanic society. An example was PROLEFEED, meaning the rubbishy\"},{\"text\":\"entertainment and spurious news which the Party handed out to the masses.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"connotation 'good' when\"},{\"text\":\"applied to the Party and 'bad' when applied to its enemies. But in\"},{\"text\":\"addition there were great numbers of words which at first sight appeared\"},{\"text\":\"to be mere abbreviations and which derived their ideological colour not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"from their meaning, but from their structure.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"So far as it could be contrived, everything that had or might have\"},{\"text\":\"political significance of any kind was fitted into the B vocabulary. The\"}]","[{\"text\":\"of people, or doctrine, or country, or\"},{\"text\":\"institution, or public building, was invariably cut down into the familiar\"},{\"text\":\"shape; that is, a single easily pronounced word with the smallest number\"}]","[{\"text\":\"derivation. In the Ministry\"},{\"text\":\"of Truth, for example, the Records Department, in which Winston Smith\"},{\"text\":\"worked, was called RECDEP, the Fiction Department was called FICDEP, the\"},{\"text\":\"Teleprogrammes Department was called TELEDEP, and so on. This was not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"done solely with the object of saving time. Even in the early decades of\"},{\"text\":\"the twentieth century, telescoped words and phrases had been one of the\"},{\"text\":\"characteristic features of political language; and it had been noticed\"}]","[{\"text\":\"abbreviations of this kind was most marked in\"},{\"text\":\"totalitarian countries and totalitarian organizations. Examples were such\"},{\"text\":\"words as NAZI, GESTAPO, COMINTERN, INPRECORR, AGITPROP. In the beginning\"}]","[{\"text\":\"but in Newspeak\"},{\"text\":\"it was used with a conscious purpose. It was perceived that in thus\"},{\"text\":\"abbreviating a name one narrowed and subtly altered its meaning, by\"},{\"text\":\"cutting out most of the associations that would otherwise cling to it.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"COMMUNIST INTERNATIONAL, for instance, call up a composite\"},{\"text\":\"picture of universal human brotherhood, red flags, barricades, Karl Marx,\"},{\"text\":\"and the Paris Commune. The word COMINTERN, on the other hand, suggests\"}]","[{\"text\":\"and a well-defined body of doctrine.\"},{\"text\":\"It refers to something almost as easily recognized, and as limited in\"},{\"text\":\"purpose, as a chair or a table. COMINTERN is a word that can be uttered\"},{\"text\":\"almost without taking thought, whereas COMMUNIST INTERNATIONAL is a phrase\"}]","[{\"text\":\"over which one is obliged to linger at least momentarily. In the same way,\"},{\"text\":\"the associations called up by a word like MINITRUE are fewer and more\"},{\"text\":\"controllable than those called up by MINISTRY OF TRUTH. This accounted not\"}]","[{\"text\":\"whenever possible, but also for the\"},{\"text\":\"almost exaggerated care that was taken to make every word easily\"},{\"text\":\"pronounceable.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"In Newspeak, euphony outweighed every consideration other than exactitude\"}]","[{\"text\":\"always sacrificed to it when it\"},{\"text\":\"seemed necessary. And rightly so, since what was required, above all for\"},{\"text\":\"political purposes, was short clipped words of unmistakable meaning which\"},{\"text\":\"could be uttered rapidly and which roused the minimum of echoes in the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"speaker's mind. The words of the B vocabulary even gained in force from\"},{\"text\":\"the fact that nearly all of them were very much alike. Almost invariably\"},{\"text\":\"these words--GOODTHINK, MINIPAX, PROLEFEED, SEXCRIME, JOYCAMP, INGSOC,\"}]","[{\"text\":\"others--were words of two or three\"},{\"text\":\"syllables, with the stress distributed equally between the first syllable\"},{\"text\":\"and the last. The use of them encouraged a gabbling style of speech, at\"},{\"text\":\"once staccato and monotonous. And this was exactly what was aimed at. The\"}]","[{\"text\":\"intention was to make speech, and especially speech on any subject not\"},{\"text\":\"ideologically neutral, as nearly as possible independent of consciousness.\"},{\"text\":\"For the purposes of everyday life it was no doubt necessary, or sometimes\"}]","[{\"text\":\"speaking, but a Party member called upon to\"},{\"text\":\"make a political or ethical judgement should be able to spray forth the\"},{\"text\":\"correct opinions as automatically as a machine gun spraying forth bullets.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"him an almost\"},{\"text\":\"foolproof instrument, and the texture of the words, with their harsh sound\"},{\"text\":\"and a certain wilful ugliness which was in accord with the spirit of\"},{\"text\":\"Ingsoc, assisted the process still further.\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"having very few words to choose from. Relative to our\"},{\"text\":\"own, the Newspeak vocabulary was tiny, and new ways of reducing it were\"},{\"text\":\"constantly being devised. Newspeak, indeed, differed from most all other\"}]","[{\"text\":\"larger every\"},{\"text\":\"year. Each reduction was a gain, since the smaller the area of choice,\"},{\"text\":\"the smaller the temptation to take thought. Ultimately it was hoped to\"},{\"text\":\"make articulate speech issue from the larynx without involving the higher\"}]","[{\"text\":\"all. This aim was frankly admitted in the Newspeak word\"},{\"text\":\"DUCKSPEAK, meaning 'to quack like a duck'. Like various other words in\"},{\"text\":\"the B vocabulary, DUCKSPEAK was ambivalent in meaning. Provided that the\"}]","[{\"text\":\"implied nothing but\"},{\"text\":\"praise, and when 'The Times' referred to one of the orators of the Party\"},{\"text\":\"as a DOUBLEPLUSGOOD DUCKSPEAKER it was paying a warm and valued compliment.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"was supplementary to the others and\"},{\"text\":\"consisted entirely of scientific and technical terms. These resembled the\"},{\"text\":\"scientific terms in use today, and were constructed from the same roots,\"},{\"text\":\"but the usual care was taken to define them rigidly and strip them of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"undesirable meanings. They followed the same grammatical rules as the\"},{\"text\":\"words in the other two vocabularies. Very few of the C words had any\"},{\"text\":\"currency either in everyday speech or in political speech. Any scientific\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the words he needed in the list devoted\"},{\"text\":\"to his own speciality, but he seldom had more than a smattering of the\"},{\"text\":\"words occurring in the other lists. Only a very few words were common to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"function of Science\"},{\"text\":\"as a habit of mind, or a method of thought, irrespective of its particular\"},{\"text\":\"branches. There was, indeed, no word for 'Science', any meaning that it\"},{\"text\":\"could possibly bear being already sufficiently covered by the word INGSOC.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"From the foregoing account it will be seen that in Newspeak the expression\"},{\"text\":\"of unorthodox opinions, above a very low level, was well-nigh impossible.\"},{\"text\":\"It was of course possible to utter heresies of a very crude kind, a\"}]","[{\"text\":\"been possible, for example, to say\"},{\"text\":\"BIG BROTHER IS UNGOOD. But this statement, which to an orthodox ear merely\"},{\"text\":\"conveyed a self-evident absurdity, could not have been sustained by\"},{\"text\":\"reasoned argument, because the necessary words were not available. Ideas\"}]","[{\"text\":\"inimical to Ingsoc could only be entertained in a vague wordless form,\"},{\"text\":\"and could only be named in very broad terms which lumped together and\"},{\"text\":\"condemned whole groups of heresies without defining them in doing so.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"for unorthodox purposes by\"},{\"text\":\"illegitimately translating some of the words back into Oldspeak. For\"},{\"text\":\"example, ALL MANS ARE EQUAL was a possible Newspeak sentence, but only\"},{\"text\":\"in the same sense in which ALL MEN ARE REDHAIRED is a possible Oldspeak\"}]","[{\"text\":\"sentence. It did not contain a grammatical error, but it expressed\"},{\"text\":\"a palpable untruth--i.e. that all men are of equal size, weight, or\"},{\"text\":\"strength. The concept of political equality no longer existed, and this\"}]","[{\"text\":\"been purged out of the word EQUAL.\"},{\"text\":\"In 1984, when Oldspeak was still the normal means of communication,\"},{\"text\":\"the danger theoretically existed that in using Newspeak words one might\"},{\"text\":\"remember their original meanings. In practice it was not difficult for\"}]","[{\"text\":\"any person well grounded in DOUBLETHINK to avoid doing this, but within\"},{\"text\":\"a couple of generations even the possibility of such a lapse would have\"},{\"text\":\"vanished. A person growing up with Newspeak as his sole language would no\"}]","[{\"text\":\"secondary meaning of 'politically\"},{\"text\":\"equal', or that FREE had once meant 'intellectually free', than for\"},{\"text\":\"instance, a person who had never heard of chess would be aware of the\"},{\"text\":\"secondary meanings attaching to QUEEN and ROOK. There would be many\"}]","[{\"text\":\"crimes and errors which it would be beyond his power to commit, simply\"},{\"text\":\"because they were nameless and therefore unimaginable. And it was to be\"},{\"text\":\"foreseen that with the passage of time the distinguishing characteristics\"}]","[{\"text\":\"more pronounced--its words growing\"},{\"text\":\"fewer and fewer, their meanings more and more rigid, and the chance of\"},{\"text\":\"putting them to improper uses always diminishing.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"When Oldspeak had been once and for all superseded, the last link with\"}]","[{\"text\":\"the past would have been severed. History had already been rewritten,\"},{\"text\":\"but fragments of the literature of the past survived here and there,\"},{\"text\":\"imperfectly censored, and so long as one retained one's knowledge of\"}]","[{\"text\":\"them. In the future such fragments, even\"},{\"text\":\"if they chanced to survive, would be unintelligible and untranslatable.\"},{\"text\":\"It was impossible to translate any passage of Oldspeak into Newspeak unless\"}]","[{\"text\":\"very simple everyday\"},{\"text\":\"action, or was already orthodox (GOODTHINKFUL would be the Newspeak\"},{\"text\":\"expression) in tendency. In practice this meant that no book written before\"},{\"text\":\"approximately 1960 could be translated as a whole. Pre-revolutionary\"}]","[{\"text\":\"literature could only be subjected to ideological translation--that is,\"},{\"text\":\"alteration in sense as well as language. Take for example the well-known\"},{\"text\":\"passage from the Declaration of Independence:\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]","[{\"text\":\"TRUTHS TO BE SELF-EVIDENT, THAT ALL MEN ARE CREATED EQUAL,\"},{\"text\":\"THAT THEY ARE ENDOWED BY THEIR CREATOR WITH CERTAIN INALIENABLE RIGHTS,\"},{\"text\":\"THAT AMONG THESE ARE LIFE, LIBERTY, AND THE PURSUIT OF HAPPINESS.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"GOVERNMENTS ARE INSTITUTED AMONG MEN,\"},{\"text\":\"DERIVING THEIR POWERS FROM THE CONSENT OF THE GOVERNED. THAT WHENEVER\"},{\"text\":\"ANY FORM OF GOVERNMENT BECOMES DESTRUCTIVE OF THOSE ENDS, IT IS THE RIGHT\"},{\"text\":\"OF THE PEOPLE TO ALTER OR ABOLISH IT, AND TO INSTITUTE NEW GOVERNMENT...\"}]","[{\"text\":\"It would have been quite impossible to render this into Newspeak while\"},{\"text\":\"keeping to the sense of the original. The nearest one could come to doing\"},{\"text\":\"so would be to swallow the whole passage up in the single word CRIMETHINK.\"}]","[{\"text\":\"ideological translation, whereby\"},{\"text\":\"Jefferson's words would be changed into a panegyric on absolute government.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"A good deal of the literature of the past was, indeed, already being\"}]","[{\"text\":\"it desirable to\"},{\"text\":\"preserve the memory of certain historical figures, while at the same time\"},{\"text\":\"bringing their achievements into line with the philosophy of Ingsoc.\"},{\"text\":\"Various writers, such as Shakespeare, Milton, Swift, Byron, Dickens, and\"}]","[{\"text\":\"therefore in process of translation: when the task had\"},{\"text\":\"been completed, their original writings, with all else that survived of\"},{\"text\":\"the literature of the past, would be destroyed. These translations were\"}]","[{\"text\":\"that they would\"},{\"text\":\"be finished before the first or second decade of the twenty-first\"},{\"text\":\"century. There were also large quantities of merely utilitarian\"},{\"text\":\"literature--indispensable technical manuals, and the like--that had to\"}]","[{\"text\":\"same way. It was chiefly in order to allow time for\"},{\"text\":\"the preliminary work of translation that the final adoption of Newspeak\"},{\"text\":\"had been fixed for so late a date as 2050.\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"},{\"text\":\"\"}]"]} 1
